('12128', 1, 'A Review of Case Studies on Climate Change Impact on Hydrologic Cycle: An Indian Perspective', 'Journal', 'Simulium himalayense is a predominant and partially anthropophilic blackfly in parts of northeastern India. Wild larvae from Tenga Valley, Arunachal Pradesh, were tested for insecticidal susceptibility by means of WHO standard bioassay procedures, using 30 min larval exposure to treated aerated water from the natural breeding sites. LC90 values expressed as ppm (= mg/1) are given in the text as 0.038 for dieldrin, 0.085 for methoxychlor, 0.205 for DDT and 0.445 for fenthion [but appear to be much greater when read from the regression lines presented graphically]. It is inferred that S. himalayense is\' susceptible\' to these insecticides [but the dosages required suggest either resistance or some discrepancy in these results when compared with other data on larval susceptibility of other Simulium spp.]. GB White', 'Susceptibility of Simulium himalayense larvae to some insecticides. SC Das, M Bhuyan, NG Das, KM Rao - Journal of Communicable Diseases, 1981 Cited by 1 Related articles All 6 versions', '1981', 'SC Das, M Bhuyan, NG Das, KM Rao', 'Journal of Communicable Diseases', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12129', 0, 'Accelerometric method for cuffless continuous blood pressure measurement', 'nan', 'Obtaining polyp size and shape is important for the medical diagnosis. In this paper, a 3-D shape reconstruction of computer vision technology is introduced in the medical diagnosis for this purpose. Some approaches based on Shape from Shading have been proposed for polyp in endoscope image. Previous approaches need some parameters such as depth parameter Z from endoscope lens to the surface point and reflectance parameter C. In the endoscope image, it is important to obtain these parameters for accurate polyp shape recovery. This paper proposes a new approach for obtaining parameters Z and C from one endoscope image where a medical suture is taken. A medical suture is used to estimate the horizontal plane locally and an observation model of medical suture is used with the horizontal plane. Two light sources endoscope observation system is assumed based on the actual endoscope for improving the accuracy of the polyp shape recovery. Experiments are conducted to validate the proposed approach.', 'Obtaining Shape from Endoscope Image Using Medical Suture with Two Light Sources HUY Iwahori, B Kijsirikul, MK Bhuyan, A Wang… Related articles', 'nan', 'Hiroyasu Usami Yuji Iwahori, Boonserm Kijsirikul, MK Bhuyan, Aili Wang, Kunio Kasugai', 'nan', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
