('12864', 0, 'New report of a sweet basil leaf blight caused by Cochliobolus lunatus in India', 'Journal', 'Significance: Reported is the highly diastereoselective organocatalytic multicomponent cascade synthesis of a series of decahydroquinolines. A mechanism is proposed involving reaction of the organocatalyst with cyclohexanone to form an imine, which then undergoes a highly stereoselective Michael-type addition to the nitroalkene. The resulting adduct then reacts with the N-Ts imine in an aza-Henry reaction, the product of which then undergoes cyclization via hemiaminalization to yield the observed products. Although no evidence is given for this mechanism, it is reasonable given the highly stereoselective nature of the reaction. Comment: Decahydroquinolines are structural components of a number of biologically active compounds and natural products (eg, pumiliotoxin: C SG Davies, G. Bhalay Tetrahedron: Asymmetry 1996, 7, 1595), and as such their synthesis has received considerable attention as …', 'Organocatalytic Cascade Synthesis of Decahydroquinolines A Rai, AK Singh, S Singh, LDS Yadav - Synfacts, 2011', '2011/4', 'A Rai, AK Singh, S Singh, LDS Yadav', 'Synfacts', '© Georg Thieme Verlag Stuttgart˙ New York', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
