('12870', 0, 'Iatrogenic Foreign Body during Extraction', 'Conference', 'nan', 'MYCOBACTERIUM AVIUM COMPLEX (MAC) INFECTION IN A PEDIATRIC RENAL TRANSPLANT RECIPIENT S Singh, FM Iorember-Acka, I Yosypiv - JOURNAL OF INVESTIGATIVE MEDICINE, 2011', '2011/2/1', 'S Singh, FM Iorember-Acka, I Yosypiv', 'JOURNAL OF INVESTIGATIVE MEDICINE', 'LIPPINCOTT WILLIAMS & WILKINS', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12871', 2, 'Enormous possibilities in big data: Trends and applications', 'Journal', 'Infrastructure based Vehicular ad hoc network has indeed increased the efficiency and accuracy of the network but at the same time it has also increased the cost required for the setup of such network. Therefore there exist needs wherein the nodes within the network itself provide security features hence eliminating the need for setting up of an expensive network. In this paper we have proposed a novel approach wherein the nodes itself can act as a central authority which will provide requesting nodes with public and private key. To improve the performance and at the same time to enhance the security and to provide confidentiality and integrity we have proposed the use of Signcryption [1, 2]. In order to take the performance of the network to next level we have proposed the use of improved Signcryption [2]. Providing improved Signcryption through nodes present within the network are the main focus of this paper.', 'A Novel Approach for Providing Security in Vehicular Adhoc Network Through Vehicles Present in the Network S Singh - International Journal of Advanced Research in …, 2011 Cited by 2 Related articles', '2011/1', 'Sumitkumar Singh', 'International Journal of Advanced Research in Computer Science', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12872', 0, 'Efficacy of entomopathogenic nematode (Heterorhabditis indica) in controlling phorid Fly, Megaselia sandhui in Agaricus bisporus', 'Journal', 'Papers downloaded from AgEcon Search may be used for non-commercial purposes and personal study only. No other use, including posting to another Internet site, is permitted without permission from the copyright owner (not AgEcon Search), or as allowed under the provisions of Fair Use, US Copyright Act, Title 17 USC', 'Meat Goat Marketing Research at Tennessee State University: An Action Plan EP Ekanem, SP Singh, F Tegegne, R Browning Jr… - Journal of Food Distribution Research, 2011 Related articles All 6 versions', '2011', 'Enefiok P Ekanem, Surendra P Singh, Fisseha Tegegne, Richard Browning Jr, Mary Mafuyai-Ekanem', 'Journal of Food Distribution Research', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12873', 0, 'Biology of phorid fly, Megaselia agarici on button mushroom Agaricus bisporus', 'Journal', '[4] So far, to the best of our knowledge, there has been no case of HIV transmission via immunoglobulin therapy, and therefore, monitoring of hepatitis B and C [yearly monitoring with hepatitis B surface antigen (HbsAg) and hepatitis C PCR for patients with antibody deficiency on long-term IVIG] is considered to be sufficient.', 'Practical issues for clinicians using high-dose intravenous immunoglobulin S Khan, S Singh - Indian Journal of Dermatology, 2011 Related articles All 9 versions', '2011', 'S Khan, S Singh', 'Indian Journal of Dermatology', 'Medknow Publications & Media Pvt. Ltd.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12874', 0, 'Relationship of scrotal circumference and hormonal levels with semen quality in Murrah buffalo young bulls', 'Journal', 'MATERIALS AND METHODS In order to achieve the objective, the data pertinent to lifetime traits on 762 Hariana cows calving during period 1966 to 2000, progeny of 23 sires maintained at Government Livestock Farm, Hisar were considered. The duration of 35 years was divided into 7 periods of five years each. The four seasons were delineated as summer (April-June), rainy (July-September), autumn (October-November) and winter (December-March) on the basis of geo-climatic conditions prevailing in the region. The traits recorded were: lactation milk yield (MY), lactation length (LL), peak yield (PY), dry period (DP), calving interval (CI) and service period (SP). Sires with at least five progenies were considered for this study. Records of cows with some specific or non–specific diseases, reproductive disorder and physical injury were excluded from the present investigation. The least-squares solutions were …', 'Genetic parameters of Lactational performance traits in Hariana cattle S Singh, ZS Rana, R Kumar, BL Pander, CS Sharma - Journal of Progressive Agriculture, 2011 Related articles', '2011', 'S Singh, ZS Rana, R Kumar, BL Pander, CS Sharma', 'Journal of Progressive Agriculture', 'Social Welfare and Integrated Development Society', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12875', 2, 'Studies of neurosecretory cells of eyestalk, brain and thoracic ganglia of Metapenaeus dobsoni (Miers, 1878) in relation to ovarian maturation', 'Journal', 'A ISTRA (\'|\' The essential oil from the rhizomes of Roma cultivar of turmeric (Curcuma longa) from Orissa was examined for its antimicrobial activity against the pathogens causing eye infections. The purpose of this study was to authenticate the use of turmeric rhizome oil against eye infections so as to giving an approach to formulate turmeric rhizome oil as potential eye drop in place of traditional antibiotics after undertaking its in Uivo pharmacological studies. Essential oil from rhizomes of homa cultivar obtained by hydrodistillation extraction method using clen evger apparatus. The antimicrobial effects of oil towards Staphylococcus aureus, f\'seudomonas aerugenosa, Candida albicans and Aspergillus niger were tested by ln hibition Zone l) iameter (IZD) test to screen the antimicrobial activity, Minimum Inhibitory Concentration (MIC) test and Minimum Killing\' l\'ime (MK\'\') test to determine the minimum concentration …', 'In vitro Validation and Phyto-constituent Analysis of Turmeric Extract: An Ethnological Alternative for Eye Treatment S Singh, BS Sathpathy, RK Sahoo, E Subudhi, S Nayak - Research Journal of Medicinal Plant, 2011 Cited by 2 Related articles', '2011', 'S Singh, BS Sathpathy, RK Sahoo, E Subudhi, S Nayak', 'Research Journal of Medicinal Plant', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12876', 0, 'A comparative study to evaluate the efficacy and safety of single dose intravenous iron carboxymaltose vs multidose iron sucrose in postpartum cases of severe iron deficiency …', 'Journal', 'Rice-wheat cropping is the predominant cropping system of Punjab. Although the system contributed immensely to the economy of Punjab but persistence growing of rice-wheat invited several problems in terms of decline in water table at an annual rate of 55 cm across the state, and also aggravation water shortfalls to the tune of 1.25 million hectare every year. It has further resulted into declining soil fertility, multiplied the problem of pest and diseases, stagnating yield and increasing weed flora. Further, the situation is worsening due to continuously increasing cost of cultivation and attaining of plateau in yield which has forced cultivations to divert the attention to look into alternate technology which may reduce the input cost besides preserving the soil health and other natural resources. In this context, reduced or zero tillage technology at farmers field has played a decisive role in sustaining the yield level by …', 'Esitmation of allocative and technical efficiencies of zero-tillage technology in rice-wheat cropping system of Punjab BK Sharma, GC Sharma, SP Singh, SP Singh - Progressive Agriculture, 2011 Related articles All 2 versions', '2011', 'BK Sharma, GC Sharma, SP Singh, Satya Pal Singh', 'Progressive Agriculture', 'Society for Recent Development in Agriculture', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12877', 0, 'Inter-Relationship among and between Sexual behaviour and Seminal Attributes of Young Sahiwal bulls', 'Journal', 'We present the measurement of multiplicity and pseudorapidity distributions of photons production at forward rapidity (−2.3 ≤ η ≤ −3.8) for Cu + Cu collisions at = 62.4 and 200 GeV. Photons are measured using the Photon Multiplicity Detector (PMD) in STAR experiment at RHIC. The distributions of (η−η beam), where η beam is beam rapidity is presented. Pseudorapidity distributions of photons at forward rapidities, when ob-served in the frame of one of the colliding particles show the signature of energy independent scaling at forward rapidities known as Limiting Fragmentation. Measurement of inclusive photons reflect the distribution for π 0 as most of the photons come from π 0 decay. Gluon saturation at initial conditions of the collisions is one of the possible explanations for this scaling. Study of system-size and incident energy dependence of …', 'Systematic study of photon production at forward rapidity in STAR N Gupta, M Sharma, S Dogra, S Singh, NK Pruthi… - Indian Journal of Physics, 2011 Related articles All 7 versions', '2011/1', 'Neeraj Gupta, M Sharma, S Dogra, S Singh, NK Pruthi, L Kumar', 'Indian Journal of Physics', 'Springer-Verlag', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12878', 0, 'Pant CMS-3A: An improved cytoplasmic male sterile line for efficient rice hybrid seed production', 'Journal', 'The present study was undertaken to evaluate the effect of some selected medicinal plants on immunomodulatory activity that comprises of screening to identify the activity of ethanolic extract of medicinal plants on humoral and cell mediated immunity(specific immune response). Experiments were conducted in vivo in Swiss albino mice. Calotropis procera ethanolic extract was found to enhance humoral immune response on 7 th day by 11% as compared to the standard control cyclophosphamide that exhibited 54% humoral immune response, whereas cell mediated immune response was observed with an enhancement in the values(18. 27%) in comparison with control cyclosporine(37. 63%).', 'IMMUNOMODULATORY ACTIVITY OF CALOTROPIS PROCERA SK Verma, SK Singh, S Singh, A Mathur - Flora and Fauna(Jhansi), 2011', '2011', 'SK Verma, SK Singh, S Singh, A Mathur', 'Flora and Fauna(Jhansi)', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12879', 7, 'Line Search Techniques by Fibonacci Search', 'Journal', 'The main aim of the present study was to investigate the species composition of Sanjay Sagar reservoir of Guna district. A limno-ichthyological study was conducted for one year (March 2007 to February 2008) and various indigenous and commercial fishes of importance were found in this reservoir. The present paper deals with the variety and abundance of fresh water fishes of reservoir.', 'Fish Fauna of Sanjay Sagar Reseirvoir of District Guna (MP) P Solanki, S Singh, IV Sharma, R Mathur - Biological Forum—An International Journal, 2011 Cited by 7 Related articles All 5 versions', '2011', 'Pradeep Solanki, Shiv Singh, IV Sharma, R Mathur', 'Biological Forum—An International Journal', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12880', 0, 'Effect of Bio-fertilizers and Inorganic Sources of NP on Quality and Yield of Kasuri Methi (Trigonella corniculata)', 'Journal', 'A field experiment was conducted to study the effect of Ni on the dry matter yield, nutrient concentration and uptake in wheat (Triticum aestivum L. cv. HUW 234) in the presence and absence of applied sulphur. A factorial combination of 16 treatments was replicated four times. Treatments comprised four levels of each of S (0, 20, 40 and 60 kg/ha) and Ni (0, 1,2 and 4 kg/ha). Applied Ni at 1 kg/ha level increased the dry matter yield significantly but at 4 kg/ha level this set in the declining trend. S and Ni interaction was significant. Dry matter yield was enhanced by Ni 1 and 2 kg/ha soil level at all levels of S but reduced at 4 kg/ha level of Ni. S concentration in plant, straw and grain increased with increasing levels of applied S in absence of Ni. Highest content was recorded at 60 kg/ha applied S in absence of Ni. When S was applied at 20 kg/ha, Ni promoted the S concentration and uptake as compared to absence of Ni …', 'Effect of ni on s uptake and dry matter yield of wheat SKS Ckandel, RP Singh, PK Yadav, SN Singh… - CROP RESEARCH, 2011 Related articles All 2 versions', '2011', 'SKS Ckandel, RP Singh, PK Yadav, SN Singh, DK Singh', 'CROP RESEARCH', 'Scientific Publishers', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12881', 5, 'An approach for grammatical constructs of Sanskrit language using morpheme and parts-of-speech tagging by Sanskrit corpus', 'Journal', 'Significantly reduction in aphid population (17.8 – 64.6 aphid/plant) was observed in Neem Seed Kernel (NSK) benzene extract (0.1%), NSK chloroform extract (0.1%), NSK acetone extract (0.1%), NSK methanol extract (0.1%), NSK butanol extract (0.1%), NSK hot water extract (5%), NSK cold water extract (5%), neem oil (2%), azadirachtin 1500 ppm (0.1%) over the control (160.6 aphid/plant). However, among the treatments significantly high aphid control and mustard yield was observed in neem seed kernel (NSK) cold water extract (5%), NSK hot water extract (5%), neem oil (2%) and azadirachtin 1500 ppm (0.1%) over the other treatments including control. All treatments were found safer to the natural enemies of mustard aphid and honeybee pollinator.', 'Bio-Effectiveness of Neem Products Against Mustard Aphid, Lipaphis Erysimi (Kalt.) in Mustard Crop SP Singh, YP Singh, A Kumar - Annals of Plant Protection Sciences, 2011 Cited by 5 Related articles All 2 versions', '2011', 'SP Singh, YP Singh, Arvind Kumar', 'Annals of Plant Protection Sciences', 'Society of Plant Protection Sciences', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12882', 0, 'Concurrent Guillain-Barre Syndrome and Transverse Myelitis in a Child following Mumps', 'Journal', 'An experiment was conducted at regional research station karnal to test the role of plant extract, neem based bio-pesticide and IGR for the management of onion thrips (Thrips tabaci L.) in onion during Rabi 2006-07 and 2007-2008. The result indicated that the Deltamethrin 2.8 EC@ 0.095% fallowed by Novaluran 10% EC@ 2 ml/lit was found effective in reducing thrips population and increasing yield.', 'Role of plant extract, neem based bio-pesticides and IGR in management of onion thrips (Thrips tabaci Lind.). BK Singh, S Singh, RP Gupta - Journal of Applied Zoological Researches, 2011', '2011', 'BK Singh, S Singh, RP Gupta', 'Journal of Applied Zoological Researches', 'Applied Zoologists Research Association', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12883', 0, 'Combining Ability Analysis in Maize (Zia-Maize)', 'Journal', 'In this paper, an inventory model with ramp type demand rate with inflation and time value of money is developed. The deterioration rate follows three-parameter Weibull distribution with the concept of life time of an item. Shortages are also allowed and unsatisfied demand is partially backlogged. The model is fairly general in practice, as the demand of some items such as fashionable items increases up to the time point of its stabilization. The backlogging rate is any non-increasing function of the waiting time up to the next replenishment. Numerical example is also considered to illustrate the results. Sensitivity analysis is also carried out.', 'AN EOQ MODEL WITH RAMP TYPE DEMAND RATE, WEIBULL DETERIORATION RATE AND PARTIAL BACKLOGGING, UNDER INFLATION D Prasad, SR Singh, MP Singh - International Journal of Mathematical Sciences, 2011 Related articles', '2011', 'Dinesh Prasad, SR Singh, MP Singh', 'International Journal of Mathematical Sciences', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12884', 1, 'Growth and developmental behaviour of Lipaphis erysimi (Kalt.) at leaf and flowering stages on different mustard genotypes.', 'Journal', 'In the present work a quick and convenient method has been described for the determination of vitamin C in pure and its pharmaceutical preparations like Celin, Sukcee, Chewcee, Citravit, Calcium Sandoz, Osto calcium, Becosule, Sorvicin & Redoxon with the use of bromine monochloride (BrCl) in acetic acid medium at 0-5 degrees C temperature. The accuracy of the method is within +/- 1%.', 'DETERMINATION OF VITAMIN C IN PURE AND PHARMACEUTICAL PREPARATIONS AT MICROSCALE A Suraiya, I Haque, S Singh - Oxidation Communications, 2011 Cited by 1 Related articles', '2011/1/1', 'A Suraiya, I Haque, S Singh', 'Oxidation Communications', 'SCIBULCOM LTD', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12885', 1, 'Screening of white button mushroom (Agaricus bisporus) strains against mushroom flies', 'nan', 'In a multi-hop mobile ad-hoc network, mobile nodes cooperate to form a network without using any infrastructure such as access points and base stations. Instead, the mobile nodes forward packets for each other\'s allowing communication among nodes outside wireless transmission range. Examples of applications for ad-hoc networks range from military operation and emergency disaster relief to community networking and interaction among meeting attendees or students during a lecture. In this ad-hoc networking applications, security is necessary to guard the network from various types of attacks. In ad-hoc networks, adverse nodes can freely join the network, listen to and/or interfere with network traffic, and compromise network nodes leads to various network failures. Since routing protocols are a fundamental tool of network-based computation, attacks on unsecured routing protocols can disrupt network …', 'A Comprehensive Survey Paper on Multi Casting Routing Protocols A Kumar, SP Singh - Research Journal of Engineering and Technology, 2011 Cited by 1 Related articles All 3 versions', '2011', 'Ajay Kumar, SP Singh', 'nan', 'A & V Publications', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12886', 1, 'Improved Biodistribution and Efficiency of Endogenous Radiotherapy by Means of Functionalized Hydrophilic Nanogels', 'Journal', 'Seasonal abundance of adult mushroom flies during January-March (2008 and 2009) revealed that the maximum population of sciarid flies was observed when the temperature was in the range of 9–20°C, whereas maximum population of phorid flies was observed in the temperature range of 18.5–23°C Phorid flies showed significant positive correlation with the temperature, whereas the sciarid flies had positive but non-significant correlation with temperature during the cropping periods of January-March (2008 and 2009).', 'Studies on seasonal abundance of adult mushroom flies G Joshi, KK Mrig, R Singh, S Singh - CROP RESEARCH, 2011 Cited by 1 Related articles All 2 versions', '2011', 'Gagan Joshi, KK Mrig, Ram Singh, S Singh', 'CROP RESEARCH', 'Scientific Publishers', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12887', 2, 'Organic Farming: A need of sustainable agriculture', 'Journal', 'Kinetic investigation on osmium(VIII)-catalysed oxidation of amino acids (alanine, proline) by alkaline solution of potassium bromate (KBrO(3)) in the presence of Hg(OAc)(2) as a scavenger for bromide ion has been carried out in the temperature range of 30-45 degrees C. The reactions exhibit zero order kinetics with respect to the substrate (alanine, pro line). The reaction follows first order dependence of the reaction both on KBrO(3) and Os(VIII). A negative effect of [OH(-)] on the rate of reaction has been found. Insignificant influence of ionic strength of the medium was observed. A suitable mechanism in conformity with the kinetic observations has been proposed and the activation parameters have been calculated.', 'KINETICS AND MECHANISM OF OSMIUM (VIII)-CATALYSED OXIDATION OF SOME AMINO ACIDS (ALANINE, PROLINE) IN THE PRESENCE OF ALKALINE POTASSIUM BROMATE S Srivastava, S Singh, P Srivastava - OXIDATION COMMUNICATIONS, 2011 Cited by 2 Related articles', '2011/1/1', 'Sh Srivastava, S Singh, P Srivastava', 'OXIDATION COMMUNICATIONS', 'SCIBULCOM LTD', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12888', 5, 'Small producers, knowledge and markets', 'Journal', 'nan', 'High performance silica fume concrete and some applications in India R Scott, SP Singh - Proceedings of the International UKIERI Concrete …, 2011 Cited by 5 Related articles', '2011', 'R Scott, SP Singh', 'Proceedings of the International UKIERI Concrete Congress New Delhi, India', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12889', 2, 'Studies on seasonal abundance of mushroom flies', 'Conference', 'Voltage sags are short duration reductions in rms voltage caused by short circuits, overloads and starting of large motors. Voltage sag is much more of a global problem. For proper analysis and mitigation of voltage sag, their characterization is important. The magnitude and durations are main characteristics of voltage sag. In this paper voltage sag and their characteristics have been presented in a comprehensive way. How voltage sags occur, what are their characteristics and impact on equipments behavior for different conditions.', 'Voltage sags and their characterization SP Singh, RK Tripathi - 2010 International Conference on Power, Control and …, 2010 Cited by 2 Related articles All 3 versions', '2010/11/29', 'Surya Prakash Singh, RK Tripathi', '2010 International Conference on Power, Control and Embedded Systems', 'IEEE', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12890', 3, 'Potential role of host tree species in determining the composition of polysaccharides of Ganoderma lucidum (Fr.) Karst.(GLPS)', 'Conference', 'Majority of the queries submitted to search engines are short and under-specified. Query expansion is a commonly used technique to address this issue. However, existing query expansion frameworks have an inherent problem of poor coherence between expansion terms and user’s search goal. User’s search goal, even for the same query, may be different at different instances. This often leads to poor retrieval performance. In many instances, user’s current search is influenced by his/her recent searches. In this paper, we study a framework which explores user’s implicit feedback provided at the time of search to determine user’s search context. We then incorporate the proposed framework with query expansion to identify relevant query expansion terms. From extensive experiments, it is evident that the proposed framework can capture the dynamics of user’s search and adapt query expansion accordingly.', 'DYNAMIC QUERY EXPANSION BASED ON USER’S REAL TIME IMPLICIT FEEDBACK SR Singh, HA Murthy, TA Gonsalves - International Conference on Knowledge Discovery and …, 2010 Cited by 3 Related articles', '2010/10/25', 'Sanasam Ranbir Singh, Hema A Murthy, Timothy A Gonsalves', 'International Conference on Knowledge Discovery and Information Retrieval', 'SCITEPRESS', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12891', 0, 'Human resource management in India: strategy, performance and complementarity', 'Journal', 'Hypoglycemic effect of acacia tortilis (100 mg/kg orally) gum extracted from seeds was evaluated in normal as well as alloxan (150 mg/kg body weight intraperitoneally) induced diabetic rats. Blood sugar levels (fasting & after oral glucose tolerance test) in normal rats were reduced after acacia torticollis gum (100 mg/kg orally) administration. Similar results were obtained when gum was administered to alloxon diabetic rats at different time intervals (0, 1 & 2 hr). Piogliotazone (4 mg/kg oral) was more potent than acacia tortilis gum in reducing blood sugar levels in alloxan diabetic rats.', 'HYPOGLYCEMIC AND ANTIHYPERGLYCEMIC ACTIVITY OF FREEZE DRIED GUM OF SEEDS OF ACACIA TORTILIS IN ALBINO RATS NK Agrawal, SP Singh, PK Gupta, J Singh - Inventi Impact: Ethnopharmacology, 2010', '2010/10/15', 'NK Agrawal, SP Singh, PK Gupta, J Singh', 'Inventi Impact: Ethnopharmacology', 'Inventi Journals (P) Ltd', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12892', 0, 'Managing the pests of oilseed crops in an ecofriendly way', 'Conference', 'nan', 'Role of yoga-asanas and pranayama on BMI in type II diabetes K Munish, M Sachdeva, T Kyizom, KP Singh, S Singh - EUROPEAN JOURNAL OF MEDICAL RESEARCH, 2010', '2010/10/13', 'K Munish, M Sachdeva, T Kyizom, KP Singh, S Singh', 'EUROPEAN JOURNAL OF MEDICAL RESEARCH', 'I HOLZAPFEL VERLAG GMBH', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12893', 3, 'Antifungal efficacy of fungicides against foliar blight of barley, Bipolaris sorokiniana.', 'Journal', 'In this paper, the two warehouse inventory problem for deteriorating items with exponential demand, shortages is considered. Holding cost is linear increasing function of time. We assume that the inventory costs in RW are higher than those in OW. In addition, shortages are allowed in the owned warehouse and the backlogging rate of unsatisfied demand is assumed to be a decreasing function of the waiting time. The objective of this study is to find the optimal inventory policies with profit maximization technique.', 'Two Storage inventory model for deteriorating items with exponential demand and shortages. SR Singh, V Kumar - International transactions in applied sciences, 2010 Cited by 3 Related articles All 2 versions', '2010/10/1', 'SR Singh, Vipin Kumar', 'International transactions in applied sciences', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12894', 0, 'Frosting Effect on Potato and its management', 'Journal', 'In this paper we successfully provide a rigorous and efficient method to derive the optimal solution for the inventory models with deteriorating items and multi dependent consumption rate. We have taken a more realistic demand rate that depends on two factors, one is time, and the other is the stock level. The stock level in itself obviously gets depleted due to the customer\'s demand. As a result, what we witness here is a circle in which the customer\'s demand is being influenced by the level of stocks available, while the stock levels are getting depleted due to the customer\'s demands. This assumption takes the customer\'s interests as well as the market forces into account. The demand rate is such that as the inventory level increases, it helps to increase the demand for the inventory under consideration. While as the time passes, demand is depends upon the various factors. The competitive nature of the market has …', 'An Inventory Model for Deteriorating Items with Time and Stock-Dependent Consumption Rate and Shortages Under Inflation and Time Discounting. S Yadav, SR Singh - International Transactions in Applied Sciences, 2010 Related articles All 2 versions', '2010/10/1', 'S Yadav, SR Singh', 'International Transactions in Applied Sciences', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12895', 1, 'Secure and efficient integrity algorithm based on existing SHA algorithms', 'Journal', 'Limitations of synthetic insecticides due to their residual toxicity opened the scope for botanicals to be considered as safe to consumers and environment. When effect of various botanicals were studied on rice it was found that marigold leaves (Tagetes erecta), were found to be most effective in controlling Sitophilus oryzae (L.) followed by neem leaves (Azadirachta indica) and it was concluded that botanicals treated grains can be saved from the Sitophilus oryzae (L.) easily; moreover, it is a cheap method to protect grains.', 'Effect of Botanicals on Sitophilus oryzae(L.) B Bhau, G Mahajan, MK Yadav, SP Singh - Environment and Ecology, 2010 Cited by 1 Related articles All 3 versions', '2010/9', 'Bandana Bhau, GAURAV Mahajan, MK Yadav, SP Singh', 'Environment and Ecology', 'nan', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12896', 0, 'CFD Analysis and Enhancement Of Heat Transfer In Rectangular Channel Using Blockage with Elongated Hole', 'Conference', 'nan', 'DIAGNOSTIC UTILITY OF FLOWCYTOMETRY IN MYELODYSPLASTIC SYNDROME: A FIRST STUDY FROM INDIA A Chopra, R Kumar, H Pati, M Mahapatra, P Mishra… - HAEMATOLOGICA-THE HEMATOLOGY JOURNAL, 2010', '2010/6/1', 'A Chopra, R Kumar, H Pati, M Mahapatra, P Mishra, T Seth, S Singh', 'HAEMATOLOGICA-THE HEMATOLOGY JOURNAL', 'FERRATA STORTI FOUNDATION', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12897', 128, 'Three level supply chain model with variable demand rate under partial trade credit policy', 'Conference', 'A number of feature selection mechanisms have been explored in text categorization, among which mutual information, information gain and chi-square are considered most effective. In this paper, we study another method known asit within class popularity to deal with feature selection based on the conceptit Gini coefficient of inequality (a commonly used measure of inequality oftextitincome). The proposed measure explores the relative distribution of a feature among different classes. From extensive experiments with four text classifiers over three datasets of different levels of heterogeneity, we observe that the proposed measure outperforms the mutual information, information gain and chi-square static with an average improvement of approximately 28.5%, 19% and 9.2% respectively.', 'Feature selection for text classification based on gini coefficient of inequality R Sanasam, H Murthy, T Gonsalves - Feature Selection in Data Mining, 2010 Cited by 128 Related articles All 10 versions', '2010/5/26', 'Ranbir Sanasam, Hema Murthy, Timothy Gonsalves', 'Feature Selection in Data Mining', 'PMLR', 2, 4, 9, 7, 13, 17),
