('12901', 1, 'High pressure phase transition and elastic properties of ytterbium compounds YbX (X= O, S, Se and Te)', 'Journal', 'Discussion Ectopic pregnancy is a life and fertility threatening event, which occurs in 1.3–2% of all reported pregnancies in the western world (Farquhar 2005). Women with a history of ectopic pregnancy have an approximately eight-fold increased risk of sustaining an ectopic pregnancy in the future (Bansgaard 2003).', 'Three ipsilateral ectopic pregnancies L Mohiyiddeen, S Singh, R El-Gawly - Journal of Obstetrics and Gynaecology, 2010 Cited by 1 Related articles All 4 versions', '2010/2/1', 'L Mohiyiddeen, S Singh, R El-Gawly', 'Journal of Obstetrics and Gynaecology', 'Taylor & Francis', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12902', 0, 'A novel MGF based capacity over “Alpha-Mu” fading distribution', 'Journal', 'Forages are the poor man’s crops and main stay of animal production. India has about 15% world’s livestock population with only 2% of the world’s geographical area. The dry and green fodder requirement in the year 1998 was estimated to be 1000 and 1200 million tonnes, respectively against the estimated availability of 550 and 350 million tonnes, respectively. Overall, the present availability of animal feeds and fodder is estimated to be 40% of the requirement (Anonymous, 1998). The country has about 4% of the cultivated area under forage crops. The forage crops include all plant species consumed by animal, thereby cover large number of grain and legume plants. The cultivated fodder crops include plant species such as sorghum, Egyptian clover (berseem), lucerne, maize, pearl millet, oats, cowpea, clusterbean (guar) mothbean and several other grasses. Among these, cowpea, clusterbean (guar) and mothbean are mainly grown in kharif season, while Egyptian clover (berseem) and lucerne are major rabi crops. Insect-pests are one of the major constraints in increasing and stabilizing the production and productivity of these forage crops. Integrated pest management (IPM) approach has been accepted worldwide for achieving sustainability in agriculture. This type of approach has numerous advantages like pesticides free produce, safety to environment, beneficial for natural enemies and low input based crop production programme especially for forage crops. Therefore, IPM is an eco-friendly approach for pest management by using all the available methods and techniques such as cultural including host plant resistance, biological …', 'Insect-pest management in legume forage crops. SP Singh, BS Chhillar - Forage Legumes, 2010 Related articles All 2 versions', '2010/2/1', 'SP Singh, BS Chhillar', 'Forage Legumes', 'Scientific Publishers', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('12903', 23, 'EFFECT OF PRE-EXISTING JUXTA-ARTICULAR OSTEOPENIA IN PATIENTS UNDERGOING TOTAL KNEE REPLACEMENT', 'Conference', 'The availability of the Internet at the click of a mouse brings with it a host of new problems. Although the World Wide Web was first started by physicists at CERN to enable collation and exchange of data, today, it is used for a wide range of applications. The requirements on bandwidth for each of the applications is also varied. An Internet Service Provider must ensure satisfaction across the entire spectrum of users. To ensure this, analysis of Internet usage becomes essential. Further, an administrator can keep a record of user\'s Internet activity and prevent unethical activities, since the Internet is also an excellent resource for providing anonymity. This analysis can also help in resource provisioning and monitoring. In this work, a web-based tool is first proposed to analyse the Internet activity. Next, data is collected from a proxy server at a campus-wide network. Traffic patterns of different types of users are studied …', 'Internet activity analysis through proxy log K Bommepally, TK Glisa, JJ Prakash, SR Singh… - 2010 National Conference On Communications (NCC), 2010 Cited by 23 Related articles All 4 versions', '2010/1/29', 'Kartik Bommepally, TK Glisa, Jeena J Prakash, Sanasam Ranbir Singh, Hema A Murthy', '2010 National Conference On Communications (NCC)', 'IEEE', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
