('13007', 2, 'CONCURRENT CHEMORADIATION THERAPY CONFERS BETTER SURVIVAL OUTCOMES IN PATIENTS WITH LOW BASELINE HPV TITRES.', 'Journal', 'Results of an analytical investigation on the flexural behaviour, of reinforced concrete (RC) beams isolated from an exterior frame sub-assemblage are presented. The performance of a beam detailed in a ductile manner as per recommendations of IS:13920- 1993 was evaluated vis-a-vis that of beams without ductile detailing. The complete response of the RC beams under monotonically increasing static loads was obtained using nonlinear finite element analysis techniques implemented with the help of ATENA 2D software. The structural response throughout the loading regime was captured in terms of the load-deflection behaviour which, in addition to the post-peak response, also characterised the mode of failure of the test beams. The crack patterns at yielding and at the end of the test were also recorded. The ductility of the test beams were evaluated in terms of the displacement ductility indices and the energy …', 'Analytical investigation on the strength and deformation characteristics of reinforced concrete beams S Kaur, B Singh, SP Singh, R Lal - Journal of the Institution of Engineers(India), Part CV …, 2007 Cited by 2 Related articles', '2007/2', 'S Kaur, B Singh, SP Singh, R Lal', 'Journal of the Institution of Engineers(India), Part CV, Civil Engineering Division', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
