('13015', 2, 'SwitchNet: Learning to switch for word-level language identification in code-mixed social media text', 'Journal', 'The experiment was conducted to find out the suitable age and position of leaf for sampling in olive a new emerging crop of Jammu and Kashmir. Leaves from three positions were collected on eighteen dates (April to December) at 15 days interval. The content of NPK in the leaves decreases continuously from top to base position of the shoot and thereby giving an average value in the middle ones. The leaves from middle positions of the shoot may therefore, be recommended for sampling to find out the status of NPK contents in olive plants. Over all effect of leaf age on NPK status indicated reduction in N and P contents up to August and increase gradually up to the October. It becomes stabilized from October and onwards while K from November and onwards. Thus November and December may be recommended best time for leaf sampling from middle position of the shoot.', 'Studies on foliar composition of nitrogen, phosphorus and potassium in olive (Olea europia L.) as affected by leafage and its position on shoot. SR Singh, A Layakat - Haryana Journal of Horticultural Sciences, 2007 Cited by 2 Related articles', '2007', 'SR Singh, Ali Layakat', 'Haryana Journal of Horticultural Sciences', 'Horticultural Society of Haryana', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
