('13059', 0, 'Autogenic drainage versus acapella for airway clearance in patients with bronchiectasis: randomised crossover trial', 'nan', 'The reductive evolution provides a pathogen minimal gene set. Due to loss of genes, for drug target identification, biochemical techniques cannot be used since these pathogens are difficult to culture. Besides classical drug targets i.e. toxins, adhesions, some novel drug targets, using a molecular phylogeny approach, can be identified. Horizontally transferred genes in bacterial pathogen from their eukaryotic host has been classified as ‘Novel drug target’, and a reusable system for identifying horizontally transferred gene has been built using a molecular phylogeny approach. Using this system, two genes have been identified in Mycobacterium leprae, which have also been identified by other methods.', 'Phylogentetic analysis of Mycobacterium leprae genome for identification of novel drug targets A Saxena, P Varadwaj, S Singh, M Jaiswal, K Misra… - 2006 Related articles All 6 versions', '2006', 'Aditya Saxena, Pritish Varadwaj, S Singh, Manoj Jaiswal, K Misra, T Lahiri', 'nan', 'CSIR', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13060', 0, 'Evaluation of similarity metrics for translation retrieval in the Hindi-English translation memory', 'Journal', 'Sixty three genotypes (45 F1s and 18 parents) were raised in a randomized block design with three replications under eight environments i.e. four locations over two seasons, to work out stability parameters for days to maturity and seed yield per plant. The variances due to genotype and genotype x environment interaction were found significant for both the characters under study, suggesting differential response of genotypes in different environments. Most of the variation could be attributed to the differences between slopes of regression for both the characters. On the basis of mean environmental indices for four locations over summer and kharif seasons, Ujjain was found best environment for days to maturity and Meerut was best environment for seed yield per plant. The summer season 2003 was found better than kharif season for days to maturity and the kharif season 2003 was better for seed yield per plant …', 'Stability and its inheritance for days to maturity and seed yield in mungbean (Vigna radiata (L.) Wilczek) SP Singh - Indian Journal of Crop Science, 2006 Related articles', '2006', 'SP Singh', 'Indian Journal of Crop Science', 'The Royal Society of Crop Science', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13061', 0, 'Exploring Contractual Relationships in Punjab: A Case Study of Potato and Basmati Paddy', 'Journal', 'The Indo-Gangetic Plain encounters several dust storms during the pre-monsoon period These dust events have significant impact on the regional scale radiation budget In the present study we have estimated the change in radiation forcing during the major dust events that occurred during the year 2005 over the background conditions for the Kanpur station The data for this study is obtained from the CIMEL sun sky radiometer deployed on the IIT Kanpur campus as a part of AERONET AErosol RObotic NETwork network The aerosol forcing calculations at Top-of-the-Atmosphere TOA and at surface were carried out using the Santa Barbara Discrete Ordinate Radiative Transfer SBDART codes The input parameters for this model such as the spectral variations of aerosol optical depth AOD single scattering albedo asymmetry factor etc have been obtained from level 1 5 processed AERONET data The obtained data is …', 'Radiative forcing due to dust events for an Indo-Gangetic Plain station, Kanpur S Singh, AK Prasad, SS Chauhan, S Singh, RP Singh… - 36th COSPAR Scientific Assembly, 2006', '2006', 'Sachchidanand Singh, Anup K Prasad, SS Chauhan, S Singh, Ramesh P Singh, Manoj K Srivastava, Risal Singh', '36th COSPAR Scientific Assembly', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13062', 0, 'Lethal Air Embolism during Javelin Removal from Skull of a Young Boy', 'Journal', 'Field trials were conducted during wet season 2000 and dry season 2001 to study the effect of cultivars and seed rates on grain yield in wet seeded rice. Among the varieties, mean maximum grain yield was recorded in IET 8887 (2.34 t ha-1) followed by IET 9219 (2.29 t ha-1), IET 8886 (2.26 t ha-1), Rasi (2.24 t ha-1), Vikas (2.22 t ha-1) and IET 9994 (2.19 t ha-1) while the lowest grain yield was recorded in IET 9818 (1.84 t ha-1). Seed rates increased grain yield significantly up to 250 kg ha-1 (2.61 t ha-1) further increase in seed rate did not increase grain yield proportionately. Weed dry matter production reduced significantly up to 300 kg seed ha-1 (57.41 g). Significantly maximum weed dry matter was recorded in cv IET 9818. IET 8887 and IET 9994 recorded higher net returns of Rs. 810 ha-1 and Rs. 610 ha-1 respectively, Among different seed rates, mean maximum net returns of Rs. 1640 ha-1 was recorded by the seed rate of 250 kg ha-1.', 'Effect of cultivars and seed rates on weed dynamics and grain yield of rice under wet seeded condition SP Singh, B Sreedevi - ORYZA, 2006 Related articles', '2006', 'SP Singh, B Sreedevi', 'ORYZA', 'ASSOC RICE REASEARCH WORKERS-INDIA', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
