('13065', 0, 'Absence of CD 9 expression in acute myeloid leukemia: possible correlation with t (8; 21)', 'Journal', 'Genetic variability, heritability and genetic advance analysis was done using 45 F1 hybrid, 45 F2 generations and his parents obtained from (10x10) diallel mating design for traits viz., Days to flowering, Plant height (cm), Number of branches per plants, Length of first fruiting nodes (cm), Length of fruits (cm), Width of fruits, Number of fruit per plant, Weight of fruits per plant (Yield per plant). The magnitude of variability was higher significantly for all genotypes under study for all the characters. The estimates of PCV were greater than GCV, indicating the importance of environmental factors. High heritability was found in F1 for days to flowering (34.07%) and length of first fruiting node (31.72%).', 'Evaluation of genetic variability, heritability and genetic advance in okra (Abelmoscus esculantus L. Moench) M Kumar, R Singh, B Singh, SP Singh - Progressive Agriculture, 2006 Related articles', '2006', 'Manoj Kumar, Rannpal Singh, B Singh, SP Singh', 'Progressive Agriculture', 'Society for Recent Development in Agriculture', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
