('13071', 0, 'TJamSpotter: Real Time Android App for Road Traffic Management.', 'Journal', 'A 4 X 4 complete diallel cross involving four broiler namely Male Line SG (Line I), Male Line SF (Line 2), Coloured Synthetic Male Line ‘CSML’ (Line 3) and Coloured Synthetic Female Line ‘CSFL’ (Line 4) was made to produce sixteen genetic groups. Body weight at 3, 5 and 7 weeks of age were measured. Heterosis was significant at 7 weeks of age. The line 4 showed the highest genera] combing ability (GCA) at 7 weeks of age. which was significantly higher than the GCA effects of other lines. The estimates of specific combining ability (SCA) were positive for body weights for the cross 1 X 4 and 2 X 3 at all the ages. The results of this investigation revealed the importance of GCA for different body weight traits. Therefore, the specialized selection within four parental strains followed by crossbreeding may be advocated for commercial broiler production.', 'Combining ability analysis for different body weight traits in broilers SP Singh, BP Singh, UB Singh, B Singh - Indian Journal of Poultry Science, 2006 Related articles', '2006', 'SP Singh, BP Singh, UB Singh, B Singh', 'Indian Journal of Poultry Science', 'Indian Poultry Science Association', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
