('13077', 0, 'Enormous possibilities in big data: Trends and applications', 'Journal', 'Members of family Asteraceae have characteristic capitulum type of inflorescence, which is single and terminal in position. Stem in the family is cylindrical. Few plants growing in the botanical garden of MSJ College, Bharatpur (India) have flat, ribbed and ribbon shaped stem bearing an abnormal inflorescence, which have five secondary capitula emerging from the main capitulum. Some plants were found to have two-three capitula on the same axis.', 'Formation of abnormal capitulum in Gellardia [Gaillardia]-a teretological report. S Singh, RK Sharma - Journal of Phytological Research, 2006', '2006', 'S Singh, RK Sharma', 'Journal of Phytological Research', 'Phytological Society', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
