('13090', 2, 'Growth and developmental behaviour of Lipaphis erysimi (Kalt.) at leaf and flowering stages on different mustard genotypes.', 'Journal', 'This paper presents a study on the fatigue strength of Steel Fibre Reinforced Concrete (SFR C). An experimental programme was conducted to obtain the fatigue lives of SFRCat various stress levels. One hundred and forty eight SFRC beam specimens of size 500 mm x 100 mm x 100 mm were tested under four-point-flexural fatigue loading. About sixty complimentary static-flexural test were also conducted to obtain the static-flexural strength prior to fatigue testing. All the fatigue tests were conducted 100 kN MTS dose loop servo-controlled universal testing machine whereas the static tests were conducted on a similar 1NSTRON machine. The specimens incorporated 1.0% volume fraction of corrugated mixed steel fibres of size 0.6 mm x 2.0 mm x 25 mm and 0.6 mm x 2.0 mm x 50 mm in different proportions. The results indicate that the distribution of fatigue life of SFRCcan be modelled by two-parameter Weibull …', 'Flexural fatigue strength and failure probability of steel fibrous concrete containing mixed fibres SP Singh, Y Mohammadi, SK Kaushik - Journal of the Institution of Engineers(India), Part CV …, 2005 Cited by 2 Related articles', '2005/5', 'SP Singh, Y Mohammadi, SK Kaushik', 'Journal of the Institution of Engineers(India), Part CV, Civil Engineering Division', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13091', 2, 'Screening of white button mushroom (Agaricus bisporus) strains against mushroom flies', 'Journal', 'The topic of Maxwell\'s equations and applications is always an interesting, though challenging area for faculty and students. This paper outlines a fast and user-interactive MATLAB-based graphical user interface (GUI) software for electromagnetic field calculations using a finite difference time domain (FDTD) algorithm. The significant reduction in computation time is achieved through a vector-based MATLAB algorithm, and additionally, the GUI user interface facilitates the understanding and modeling of electromagnetic field effects. This paper is primarily directed at teachers and students involved in advanced electromagnetic and RF design studies at the graduate level, for example, courses in microwave engineering, power engineering and biomedical engineering. Typical electromagnetic simulation studies are presented in this paper to illustrate the efficacy and userfriendly nature of the software.', 'A student-accessible graphical user interface-based FDTD algorithm for visualization of electromagnetic fields S Singh, S Bhatt, S Kapoor, A Bhavsar, BP Kumar - International Journal of Engineering Education, 2005 Cited by 2 Related articles All 5 versions', '2005/1/1', 'S Singh, S Bhatt, S Kapoor, A Bhavsar, BP Kumar', 'International Journal of Engineering Education', 'TEMPUS PUBLICATIONS', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
