('13095', 3, 'Studies on seasonal abundance of mushroom flies', 'Journal', 'The study of genetic divergence exploiting two powerful statistical techniques of multivariate analysis was performed in 20 genotypes of C, lancealala from diverse geographical sources, which on the basis of 11 characters was grouped into 7 clusters. Genetic divergence was not found to be related with geographic diversity of this species. The genotypes falling in cluster IV had the maximum intra-cluster divergence. The Mexican genotypespossessed substantial diversity. The characters such as test weight, fruit number and seed yi material. eld exerted marked inﬂuence on genetic diversity in this', 'Genetic divergence in Cuphea lanceolata-a medicinal plant R Rameshkumar, SP Singh - J Med Aromat Plant Sci, 2005 Cited by 3 Related articles', '2005', 'R Rameshkumar, SP Singh', 'J Med Aromat Plant Sci', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13096', 0, 'Potential role of host tree species in determining the composition of polysaccharides of Ganoderma lucidum (Fr.) Karst.(GLPS)', 'Journal', 'Intercropping system has been found productive and remunerative under rainfed conditions of Bundelkhand. Pigeonpea is a long duration widely spaced crop, thus it privides scope of harnessing the benefit of short duration inter crops like soybean. It helps to harvest the potentiality of environment for increasing production as well as profit. The present experiment was aimed to assess the effect of intercropping management in pigeon pea under rainfed conditions of Bundelkhand. A field experiment in a randomized block dsign with four replications was conducted on kabar soil (black soil) under rainfed conditions for three years (2000-01, 2001-02, 2002-03) at Regional Agriculture Research Station, Bharari, Jhansi. The soil was light clay loam with low organic matter (0.25%), medium available phosphorus (12 kg/ha) and high in potassium (22 kg/ha), and with 7.8 pH.', 'Inter-cropping of soybean with pigeonpea under rainfed conditions P Kumar, SP Singh, SK Swarnkar - Progressive Agriculture, 2005 Related articles', '2005', 'Premed Kumar, SP Singh, SK Swarnkar', 'Progressive Agriculture', 'Society for Recent Development in Agriculture', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
