('13138', 0, 'Transliteration of english loanwords and named-entities to manipuri: Phoneme vs grapheme representation', 'Journal', 'The value of an inbred line on its ability to produce superior hybrids in combination with other inbreds. Combining ability analysis helps in the evaluation of hybrids in terms of their genetic value and the selection of suitable parents for hybridization. The average performance of a genotype in a series of hybrid combinations is termed as general combining ability. Thus sca refers to the deviation of a particular cross from the gca. Rohini found to be good general combiner NDR-8501 x Mathura Rai was found to be good specific combiner for days to maturity, number of secondary branches, number of siliquae on main raceme and seed yield. Top ranking crosses selected on the basis of significant desirable sca effect involved high, medium and low general combiners.', 'Genetics of grain yield and its components in Indian mustard (Brassica juncea L.) Czern and Coss. R Kumar, M Singh, YP Singh, SP Singh - Progressive Agriculture, 2004 Related articles', '2004', 'Rajeev Kumar, Mahak Singh, YP Singh, SP Singh', 'Progressive Agriculture', 'Society for Recent Development in Agriculture', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13139', 3, 'Exploiting reciprocity toward link prediction', 'Journal', 'The material from a 10 x 10 half diallel crosses (excluding reciprocals) involving white seeded exotic maize inbreds was raised under rainfedcondition. Analysis of variance revealed highly significant differences for GCA and SCA effects for ten characters studied. Among the parents, CML-369 CML-368 were found to have negative GCA effect for days to 50% silking and days to maturity. Parent CML-367 was found to have highest significant and negative GCA effect for plant height and ear height and highest positive significant for ear girth, ear length and 100 kernel weight. The best general combiner Parents for grain yield were CML-78 and CML-311. The four cross combinations. CML-78 x CML-369, CML-368 x CML-311, CML-78 x CML-311 and CML-371 x CML-374 were found to have highly significant and positive SCA effects for grain yield and other polygenic traits viz. ear girth, ear length, kernel/rows, kernel …', 'Combining ability for grain yield and its components in exotic white seed colour maize (Zea mays L.) under rainfed environment SB Singh, SP Singh - Progressive Agriculture, 2004 Cited by 3 Related articles', '2004', 'SB Singh, SP Singh', 'Progressive Agriculture', 'Society for Recent Development in Agriculture', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
