('13143', 5, 'Effect of language independent transcribers on spoken language identification for different Indian languages', 'nan', 'The paper presents a study on the fatigue strength of steel fibre reinforced concrete (SFRC) containing different volume fractions, aspect ratios and types of steel fibers, for various Levels of the fatigue stress. The fatigue test data available in literature has been used for analysis. The test data is used to generate the SN curves and an Equation is proposed by regression analysis to predict the flexural fatigue strength of SFRC. A probabilistic approach issued to predict the fatigue reliability of SFRC. The fatigue-life distributions of SFRC at a given stress level, is shown to approximately follow the two-parameter Weibull distribution. The SN relationships have been used to obtain the parameters of the Weibull distribution. Mean and Design fatigue lives have been computed for different stress levels for SFRC with Different combinations of fibres, corresponding to different probabilities of failure.', 'Prediction of mean and design fatigue lives of steel fibrous concrete using SN relationships SP Singh, S Goel, R Lal, SK Kaushik - 2004 Cited by 5 Related articles All 6 versions', '2004/1/1', 'SP Singh, Sanjay Goel, Roshan Lal, SK Kaushik', 'nan', 'ASIAN JOURNAL OF CIVIL ENGINEERING (BUILDING AND HOUSING)', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13144', 0, 'Word polarity detection using syllable features for manipuri language', 'Journal', 'The small hydro is environmental friendly and provides operational flexibility suitable for peak support to the local grid as well as for stand-alone operation in isolated and remote area. This paper presents the various techniques used for Electronic Load Controller. Attempt has also been made to compare the SHP system having conventional type governing with SHP system having Electronic Load Controller. The simulated results of various circuits also given.', '63. Cost Effective Governing of Micro Hydropower Plant by Using Electronic Load Controller SP Singh, SN Singh - Water and Energy Abstracts, 2004', '2004', 'Surendra Pratap Singh, SN Singh', 'Water and Energy Abstracts', 'Central Board of Irrigation and Power', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13145', 0, 'Automatic pause marking for speech synthesis', 'Journal', 'Pigeon pea [Cajanus cajan (L.) Millsp.] is an important pulse crop of India, which was found to suffer from leaf blight caused by Alternaria tenuissima (Kunz ex Pers.) Wiltshire. The severity of disease varied from 13.7 to 38.5% in different areas of DP and causing severe losses around Kanpur and adjoining areas during September 1997 to October 1998. A study was therefore, conducted to determine the survival of the pathogen through diseased plant debris.', 'Survival of Alternaria tenuissima Causing Leaf Spot of Pigeon Pea in Diseased Plant Debris SP Singh - Annals of Plant Protection Sciences, 2004 Related articles All 2 versions', '2004', 'SP Singh', 'Annals of Plant Protection Sciences', 'Society of Plant Protection Sciences', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13146', 0, 'Effect of planting date on incidence of early blight (Alternaria Solanai) and yield of potato due to climate change', 'Journal', 'We have developed thermal models of oceanic crustal accretion at fast-spreading ridges that explicitly include petrological variation and allow the distribution of crystallisation and hydrothermal cooling to be varied. These models are used to relate geophysical observations from active ridges to petrological and geological observations from ophiolites. We ran a large number of models with different distributions of crystallisation and found that this distribution is not strongly constrained by a combination of seismic tomography and large-scale petrological observations from the Oman ophiolite. When constraints from seismic reflection and compliance surveys are also included, we find that models where 25--100% of the lower crust is formed by crystallisation in the shallow melt lens and 25--100% of the lower crust crystallises at its final depth can match the observations. Therefore, further observations are required to …', 'Crustal Accretion and Cooling of the Lower Crust at Fast-Spreading Ridges: Thermal Models Consistent with Petrological and Geophysical Observations from Active Ridges and Ophiolites J Maclennan, T Hulme, S Singh - AGU Fall Meeting Abstracts, 2003', '2003/12', 'J Maclennan, T Hulme, S Singh', 'AGU Fall Meeting Abstracts', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13147', 0, 'Automatic syllabification for manipuri language', 'Journal', 'It is well established that effluents discharged from the distilleries have been creating environmental problems. Attempt has been made to study the effect of distillery effluent on seed germination, seedling growth and chlorophyll content in Triticum aestivum. Total chlorophyll were found to be non significant during ear emergence and highly significant (P < 0.001) during maturity stage in 25% effluents. It is suggested that distilleries effluent contains high amount of organic matter, therefore not suitable for irrigation purposes without treatment, whereas diluted concentrations of distillery effluents may be used for agricultural purposes.', 'Impact Of Distillery Effluent On Chlorophyll Content In Wheat(Triticum aestivum) S Singh - Journal of Ecophysiology and Occupational Health, 2003 All 2 versions', '2003/12', 'S Singh', 'Journal of Ecophysiology and Occupational Health', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13148', 0, 'Generating Manipuri English pronunciation dictionary using sequence labelling problem', 'Conference', 'In the present work a novel approach for Active Noise Control (ANC) is attempted. A structural panel used as a secondary source for active noise control in a rectangular duct is developed and tested. The structural panel is a square Aluminum trim panel, which is fixed on a steel frame vertically and excited by an electrodynamic exciter. The structural panel has many merits as an acoustic source over traditional loud speakers: it is simple in geometry, lower mass, easy in construction and requires only a simple modification of materials already installed on the duct. The vibration response and acoustic radiation response of the structural panel are studied for a simply supported boundary condition, when panel is subjected to less than 350 Hz harmonic excitation. Real time active noise control experiments are performed in a laboratory using the active structural panel as secondary source. Local attenuation of sound …', 'Noise control in a rectangular duct using active structural panel K Kannan, SP Singh, KK Pujara - Smart Materials, Structures, and Systems, 2003 Related articles All 5 versions', '2003/10/14', 'K Kannan, SP Singh, KK Pujara', 'Smart Materials, Structures, and Systems', 'SPIE', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13149', 0, 'Personalised pagerank as a method of exploiting heterogeneous network for counter terrorism and homeland security', 'Journal', 'The dermal toxicity of six synthetic detergents was studied by guinea pig immersion test. The animals were treated for four consecutive days for 1.5 hour daily to 2.5% (wt/vol) concentration of detergents separately. The exposed animals showed erythema, oedema, scaling and cracking of skin along with decrease in body weight. The blood parameters such as hemoglobin, hematocrit, glucose and serum aspartate and alanine amenotransferases did not differ from that of control animals.', 'Toxicity of Commercially Available Synthetic Detergents AK Mathur, S Singh, A Singh - Environment and Ecology, 2003', '2003/6', 'AK Mathur, S Singh, A Singh', 'Environment and Ecology', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13150', 24, 'A time aware method for predicting dull nodes and links in evolving networks for data cleaning', 'Journal', 'Searching the World Wide Web considered as a digital library having widely distributed information for news, advertisements, education, government, e-commerce and many information poses a great challenge. Keyword based search engines like Lycos [12], Excite [15], Northern Light [16], Alta Vista [14] often suffers from lack of quality pages. Information on the Web is authored by millions of Web creators having a variety of backgrounds, knowledge and interests. Web can be viewed as a graph, where pages are the nodes and edges are the hyperlinks. In recent studies, hyperlinks are being actively used to improve Web search performance [2, 5, 11, 8, 12]. Hyperlinks are created by web creators based on their interest on the cited pages and/or relevance to the cited pages with their pages. Although, hyperlink (or citation) based search engines like Google [1] provides better search quality, communities [3] and …', 'An approach to confidence based page ranking for user oriented web search D Mukhopadhyay, D Giri, SR Singh - ACM SIGMOD Record, 2003 Cited by 24 Related articles All 11 versions', '2003/6/1', 'Debajyoti Mukhopadhyay, Debasis Giri, Sanasam Ranbir Singh', 'ACM SIGMOD Record', 'ACM', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
