('13163', 1, 'Evaluation of similarity metrics for translation retrieval in the Hindi-English translation memory', 'Journal', 'To fill up wide gap between demand and supply of healthy seed lies in technology of production of \'Home Grown Seed\' by farmers to make the country self-sufficient in seed requirement. Punjab, Haryana, Uttar Pradesh, Bihar and parts of Madhya Pradesh in plains, and high hills above 2,500 m in the north-western Himalayan region are suitable for growing high-quality seed potatoes. Fields infested with common scab, brown rot, wart, golden and root-knot nematodes, and areas having short crop period and high insect vector problems are not suitable for potato seed production.', 'Home-grown potato seed production S Singh - Indian Horticulture (India), 2003 Cited by 1 Related articles', '2003', 'S Singh', 'Indian Horticulture (India)', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
