('13171', 0, 'An outpatient quality improvement program increased advance directive discussions that identified a health care proxy or surrogate decision maker', 'Conference', 'We developed a flow cytometric methodology to measure the affinity and kinetics of L-selectin binding to their natural ligands on neutrophils (PMNs) and to synthetic selectin-ligand analogues under physiologically relevant conditions. The synthetic molecules tested include the sLe/sup x/ oligosaccharide, selected sLe/sup x/ analogues and core-2 based sialylated and sulfated sugars expressed on the natural selectin-ligands, including GlyCAM-1 and PSGL-1. Quantitative analysis was performed to determine the affinity constant (K/sub d/) and binding rates of these molecules. We observed that: i) divalent soluble L-selectin bound their ligands on neutrophils (predominantly PSGL-1) with an on-rate of 9.5/spl times/10/sup 4//M/ss and off-rate of 2.3/spl times/10/sup -3//s. ii) The free acid forms of sialyl lewis-X (sLe/sup x/-OH) and sialyl lewis-a (sLe/sup a/-OH) were /spl sim/2-4 fold poorer inhibitors of L-selectin …', 'Affinity and kinetic analysis of L-selectin binding to their natural ligands and to synthetic oligosaccharides M Beauharnois, K Matta, S Singh, S Neelamegham - Proceedings of the Second Joint 24th Annual …, 2002 Related articles', '2002/10/23', 'M Beauharnois, K Matta, S Singh, S Neelamegham', 'Proceedings of the Second Joint 24th Annual Conference and the Annual Fall Meeting of the Biomedical Engineering Society][Engineering in Medicine and Biology', 'IEEE', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
