('13191', 0, 'Concurrent Guillain-Barre Syndrome and Transverse Myelitis in a Child following Mumps', 'Journal', 'Cuphea genus (Fam. Lytharaeae) is important minor annual oil seed crop of tropical to sub-tropical American origin. It is rich source of medium chain fatty acids (C 8: 0 to C 16: 0). This genus is an excellent natural source of caprylic (C 8: 0) and Capric (C 10: 0) acids which are currently obtained from petroleum products and also rich source of lauric acid (C: 12: 0), presently derived from coconut and palm kernel oils (Graham et al.\': Robbelin and Hirsinger?; Khanna and Singh?; Knapp “; Pandey et al.\') Cuphea is newly tapped oil seed crop and due to diversity in different fatty acids in one crop, it is supposed to be an important oil seed crop of 21st century (Khanna and Singh and Singh at al.). Though the crop is very valuable on technological viewpoint but very little genetic improvement has been made so far (Singh and Shukla’). Morphological characters like plant spread. Primary and secondary branches/plant are important in contributing towards the economic yield', 'Diallel analysis for some morphological traits in Cuphea procumbens SP Singh, M Singh - … NATIONAL ACADEMY OF SCIENCES INDIA SECTION …, 2002 Related articles', '2002', 'SP Singh, MEENAKSHI Singh', 'PROCEEDINGS-NATIONAL ACADEMY OF SCIENCES INDIA SECTION B', 'NATIONAL ACADEMY OF SCIENCES, INDIA', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
