('13199', 0, 'Potential role of host tree species in determining the composition of polysaccharides of Ganoderma lucidum (Fr.) Karst.(GLPS)', 'Journal', 'The forage sorghum suffers huge loss because of severe infection of Atherigona soccata, Chilo partellus, and Stenodiplosis sorghicola in northern India. Therefore to increase and stabilise forage sorghum production and productivity, there is need to follow IPM Module in forage sorghum cultivation and use disease-reistant varieties viz. SSG 59-3 forage sorghum to reduce shootfly incidence etc.', 'Management of insect pests in forage sorghum SP Singh, RPS Grewal - Indian Farming (India), 2002', '2002', 'SP Singh, RPS Grewal', 'Indian Farming (India)', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
