('13204', 0, 'Secure and efficient integrity algorithm based on existing SHA algorithms', 'Journal', 'Present study includes various histochemical changes in the mucosa of pyloric stomach of bat, Rhinopoma microphyllum following the administration of CCl sub(4). It was noticed that acid phosphatase-rich lysosomal activity appears to be quite intense in the pyloric glands where mucosal folds and glandular epithelial lining get darkly stained in normal bat, R. microphyllum. However, in CCl sub(4)-treated bat, R. microphyllum acid phosphatase activity seems to be markdly increased accompained by structural disorganization of mucosal folds, erosion of surface epithelial cells and nuclear fragmentation in cells of pyloric glands. A possible functional significance of differential acid phosphatase localization and various cyto-architectural changes in relation to CCl sub(4)-induced toxicity in pyloric stomach of bat has been stated.', 'Some histochemical changes in the pyloric stomach of carbon tetrachloride treated bat, Rhinopoma microphyllum SP Singh, R Singh - Journal of Ecophysiology and Occupational Health, 2001', '2001/12', 'SP Singh, R Singh', 'Journal of Ecophysiology and Occupational Health', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13205', 0, 'CFD Analysis and Enhancement Of Heat Transfer In Rectangular Channel Using Blockage with Elongated Hole', 'Journal', 'Molybdenum is a broad spectrum metal, highly useful in industrial as well as biological systems. This metal is also toxic in certain circumstances. Following high oral exposure, it may cause molybdenosis, gastrointestinal cancers and reproductive effects in cattles and humans. This article shows the accumulation of molybdenum in body tissues and its testicular toxicity was investigated by studying some biochemical and morphological parameters. The specific activity of g-glutamyl transpeptidase decreases increases while lactate dehydrogenase and sorbitol dehydrogenase increases. Male mediated experiments also shows loss of weight and crown rump length in embryo.', 'Toxicity and fate of molybdenum- health problems R Pandey, SP Singh - Journal of Ecophysiology and Occupational Health, 2001', '2001/12', 'R Pandey, SP Singh', 'Journal of Ecophysiology and Occupational Health', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
