('13236', 3, 'Network sampling using k-hop random walks for heterogeneous network embedding', 'Journal', 'A field experiment was conducted at the Research Farm of Agricultural Botany, Meerut University, Meerut, Uttar Pradesh, India during the kharif season of 1991. The correlation coefficients were estimated among all the 7 characters (plant height, biological yield, number of pods per plant, number of seeds per pod, seed yield per plant, 100-seed weight, harvest index) in 7 parents and F 2 generations of mung bean. The maximum positive and significant correlation coefficient (0.790) in non-segregating generation, was observed between number of pods per plant and seed yield per plant, whereas, in the segregating (F 2) generation, maximum positive and significant correlation (0.874) was found between seed yield and harvest index in the cross MG-46, PDM84-146. Seed yield per plant had positive and significant correlation with biological yield, number of pods and harvest index of the parents, with number of pods per plant in all the F 2 populations, with plant height and biological yield of the cross PS-16× ML-5 and with harvest index of two cross combinations. It is concluded that the number of pods per plant was consistently associated with seed yield and therefore, should be considered for improving the seed yield in segregating generations of mung bean.', 'Study of correlation in segregating and non-segregating populations of mungbean (Vigna radiata (L.) Wilczek). SB Singh, SP Singh - Applied Biological Research, 2000 Cited by 3 Related articles', '2000', 'SB Singh, SP Singh', 'Applied Biological Research', 'Centre for Advancement of Applied Sciences', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13237', 3, 'Prioritized Named Entity Driven LDA for Document Clustering', 'Journal', 'DISCUSSION Mucor mycosis is a dreaded fungal infectioncaused by fungi of the order mucorales and German Rhizipine, Absidia and Mucor.[1] These fungi are usually found in vegetative and organic matter and have minimal intrinsic pathogenicity. However it can cause serious and fatal infection in immunocompromised conditions especially in patients who have diabetic ketoacidosis, viral hepatitis, chronic renal failure and post transplant patients on immunosuppressive therapy.[2-4] The usual portal of entry includes infection through inhalation, ingestion, contamination of skin wounds or via vascular channels such as intravenous drips. The clinical presentation of mucor mycosis depending on the portal of entry, includes rhinocerebral, pulmonary, gastrointestinal, disseminated and miscellaneous forms involving isolated organs like bone, heart and kidneys.', 'Mucormycosis of transplanted kidney BQ Ponnappa, S Singh, PM Korath - Bombay Hosp J, 2000 Cited by 3 Related articles All 2 versions', '2000', 'BQ Ponnappa, S Singh, PM Korath', 'Bombay Hosp J', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
