('13246', 3, 'Effect of language independent transcribers on spoken language identification for different Indian languages', 'Journal', 'Amongst the fast expanding frontiers of Agricultural Biotechnology, the pest control arena is one of the most active. The motivation comes from the heavy worldwide crop damage (20-30%) caused by phytophagous insects (not accounting for loss due to viral and mycoplasma diseases which are transmitted by insects) inspite of advanced plant protection measures, chiefly, through chemicals. It is now possible to identify and isolate', 'Application of biotechnology in bio-intensive integrated pest management SP Singh - Biotechnology in horticultural and plantation crops, 2000 Cited by 3 Related articles', '2000', 'SP Singh', 'Biotechnology in horticultural and plantation crops', 'Malhotra Publishing House', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13247', 0, 'Word polarity detection using syllable features for manipuri language', 'Journal', 'This workshop brought together forest management personnel from various parts of the Hindu Kush-Himalayas. The basis of their discussions was the people-centred forest policies that have emerged in many countries of the region and their objectives of supporting and strengthening participatory forest management to ensure that the needs of mountain people receive the priority they deserve. The policies, along with their constraints and opportunities were discussed in depth, guided by papers provided by the participants themselves. This volume on India is one of 6: the first contained the workshop proceedings themselves, and the other 4 cover studies from China, the Eastern Himalayas, Nepal and Pakistan. The Indian studies are made up of 5 papers by different authors: Challenges to the management of forests in the mountain regions of India (Oberai. CP); Training issues in joint forest management in the Hindu Kush-Himalayan states of India (Gangopadhyay, PB); Status of participatory forest management: implications for policy and human resources\' development in Himachal Pradesh, India (Gulati, AK); Participatory forest management: implications for policy and human resources\' development in Jammu and Kashmir, India (Patnaik, P.; Singh, S.); and Participatory forest management: implications for policy and human resources\' development in the Uttarakhand Himalayas, Uttar Pradesh, India (Ghildiyal, MC; Arup Banerjee).', 'Participatory forest management: implications for policy and human resources\' development in the Hindu Kush-Himalayas. Vol IV: India.[Studies and papers from a workshop held 7-12 May, Kunming, China]. PB Gangopadhyay, AK Gulati, P Patnaik, S Singh… - Participatory forest management: implications for policy …, 2000', '2000', 'PB Gangopadhyay, AK Gulati, P Patnaik, S Singh, MC Ghildiyal, Banerjee Arup', 'Participatory forest management: implications for policy and human resources\' development in the Hindu Kush-Himalayas. Vol IV: India.[Studies and papers from a workshop held 7-12 May, Kunming, China].', 'International Centre for Integrated Mountain Development', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13248', 2, 'Automatic pause marking for speech synthesis', 'Journal', 'In order to elicit maturity gradients, a sample of 786 boys of Gaddi tribe were studied from Bharmour valley of Chamba District of Himachal Pradesh. Various anthropometic measurements were taken on each subject who were between 4 and 20 years and the means were obtained at each age group. These means were transformed into percentages of the mature values for that parameter. Head as a rule is advanced in maturity to trunk which in turn is advanced to forearm and upper arm. In the case of lower extremity, foot length is ahead in maturation to lower leg length and the thigh length. In the case of hand and foot, it is the length which is the ahead in maturity to that of its breadth. These sequences of maturation which conform to the general rules of maturation have implications during childhood for manipulation and in child behaviour.', 'Maturity gradients in Gaddi Rajput boys SP Singh - Advances in Human Biology at the Turn of the …, 2000 Cited by 2 Related articles', '2000', 'SP Singh', 'Advances in Human Biology at the Turn of the Millennium', 'Punjabi University Publication Bureau, Patiala', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
