('13265', 2, 'Autogenic drainage versus acapella for airway clearance in patients with bronchiectasis: randomised crossover trial', 'Journal', 'Seven neem formulations namely achook, neemax, neemgold, rakshak, azadirachtm, neem seed kernel extract and neem oil when tested along with conventional insecticide chlorpyriphos against rice leaffolder, Cnaphalocrocis medinalis Guenee in North Bihar agroclimatic conditions during kharif 1993 and 1994, revealed that rakshak was the most effective treatment in containing the leaf damage due to rice leaffolder and was comparable to chlorpyriphos, achook and neemax treatments. All the neem formulations significantly increased the grain yield of rice, rakshak giving the highest yield of 37.29 q ha−1 which was not significantly different from chlorpyriphos treatment (36.49 q ha−1).', 'Efficacy of some Neem Formulations against Rice Leaffolder, Cnaphalocrocis medinalis Guenee in North Bihar Agro-climatic Conditions SP Singh, AK Singh, SP Singh - Pesticide Research Journal, 1999 Cited by 2 Related articles All 2 versions', '1999', 'SP Singh, AK Singh, SP Singh', 'Pesticide Research Journal', 'Society of Pesticide Science, India', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13266', 0, 'Evaluation of similarity metrics for translation retrieval in the Hindi-English translation memory', 'Journal', 'The emergence of high-power semiconductor devices such as insulated-gate bipolar (IGBTs) or injectionenhanced gate transistors (IEGTs) and gate-commutated turnoff (GCT) thyristors or integrated gate-commutated thyristors (IGCTs) enables large static converters to expand into utility and industry applications. For instance, a±80-kV 50-MW HVDC transmission system based on a string of many IGBTs connected in series was commissioned in 1999. This paper presents the status of large static converters, with the focus on their applications to the utility and industry. The paper also describes their future prospects and directions in the 21st century.', 'Large Static Converters Used for Industry and Utility Applications SP Singh, RK Tripathi - Development, 1999 Related articles', '1999', 'Surya Prakash Singh, Ramesh Kumar Tripathi', 'Development', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
