('13268', 6, 'Lethal Air Embolism during Javelin Removal from Skull of a Young Boy', 'Journal', 'Interactive effets of initial profile moisture status and nitrogen levels on water use pattern of dryland barley have been evaluated. Three levels of initial profile (1.2 m) moisture status viz. wet (100% field capacity), moderately wet (50% field capacity) and dry (rainfed) and four levels of basal dose of 0, 40, 60 and 80 kg N ha-1 were taken, respectively as main and subplot treatments: Biomass production at various cropping stages and grain yieldwere recorded. Periodical and cumulative actual evapotranspiration (ET) were computed during the entire cropping period. During 15 to 60 days after sowing (DAS), biomass values were of higher magnitude under wet than the dry regime. However, biomass at 105 DAS and grain yield showed the opposite trend. Periodical Et loss was, in general, higher under wet regime as compared to others and the difference was wider up to 75 DAS. Role of nitrogen on ET loss was more pronounced under wet regime as compared to dry one.', 'Influence of initial profile water status and nitrogen doses on yield and evapotranspiration rate of dryland barely S Sarkar, SK Singh, SR Singh, AP Singh - Journal of the Indian Society of Soil Science (India)., 1999 Cited by 6 Related articles All 2 versions', '1999', 'S Sarkar, SK Singh, SR Singh, AP Singh', 'Journal of the Indian Society of Soil Science (India).', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
