('13270', 0, 'Tree Formation Using Coordinate Method', 'Journal', 'Nifedipine therapy 10 mg ED orally, carried out in 14 PIH pregnant subjects on comparison with 10 normal pregnant control clearly indicates as a valuable therapeutic tool. Platelet serotonin uptake was markedly decreased with reduced serotonin content after 2 weeks, with increased platelet numbers. Clinically it controlled blood pressure, oedema and proteinuria. Calcium level was statistically decreased in post-therapy group along with potassium level with unaltered sodium level in blood. This study augmented the beneficial effects of nifedipine on biochemical and clinical parameters in PIH subjects.', 'Effect of nifedipine on platelet serotonergic mechanisms in pregnancy induced hypertension VR Gujrati, S Singh, K Shanker, C Vati - Biogenic amines, 1999 All 2 versions', '1999/1/1', 'VR Gujrati, S Singh, K Shanker, Chandra Vati', 'Biogenic amines', 'VSP', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0);
