('13281', 0, 'Two-phase flow instability and bifurcation analysis of inclined multiple uniformly heated channels-15107', 'Journal', 'The phytotoxic effects of Nickel (Ni) have been known for a long time (Mishra & Kar 1974). Nickel concentration in plants is affected by many factors such as soil properties, climatic conditions, plant species and cultivars, etc. Although information on the uptake of Ni by various plants is available, systematic studies about the inter-specific differences in the Ni accumulation and tolerance by forage species are lacking. Therefore, the present study was conducte; d to compare the accumulation of Ni by selected forage species grown in a coarse textured soil.', 'Accumulation of nickel in selected forage species SP Singh, YK Nayyar - Journal of the Indian Society of Soil Science, 1998 Related articles All 4 versions', '1998', 'SP Singh, YK Nayyar', 'Journal of the Indian Society of Soil Science', 'Indian Society of Soil Science', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
