('13331', 5, 'Manipuri-English machine translation using comparable corpus', 'Book', 'Synthetic pesticides which are used for managing these pests suffer from serious drawbacks. A recent estimate by World Health Organisation (WHO) puts the number of acute poisoning due to use of synthetic pesticides at threee million with 220,000 deaths (Hoddy, 1993). It is also calculated that as many as 25 million agricultural workers in developing countries have episode of pesticide poisoning but few seek medical attention (Hoddy, 1993).', 'Neem for management of insect pests: advantages and disadvantages RP Singh, S Singh - Recent Advances in Indian Entomology, 1996 Cited by 5 Related articles', '1996', 'RP Singh, Shivendra Singh', 'Recent Advances in Indian Entomology', 'APC Publications Pvt. Ltd New Delhi, India', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
