('13344', 0, 'Transliteration of english loanwords and named-entities to manipuri: Phoneme vs grapheme representation', 'Journal', 'GPF2, a new desi chickpea variety derived by the pedigree method from GL769 × H75-35, was released for cultivation in the North Western Plain Zone in 1994. In 36 trials at 10-13 locations during 1991-92 to 1993-94, GPF2 gave an average seed yield of 2181 kg/ha compared with 1967 and 1938 kg/ha for control cultivars C235 and PBG1, an increase of 10.9 and 12.5%, respectively. In 12 trials during 1991-92 to 1993-94, the incidence of Fusarium wilt (F. oxysporum f.sp. ciceris) and root rot (Macrophomina phaseolina) was on average 17.2% in GPF2 compared to 86.4, 37.9 and 43.1% for control varieties JG62, C235 and PBG1, respectively. For GPF2 the incidence of Ascochyta blight (A. rabiei) was similar to control cultivars PBG1 and GNG146, but low compared to C235. Gray-mould (Botrytis cinerea) occurrence was similar to the control cultivars. Pod borer (Helicoverpa armigera) incidence was 38% in GPF2 …', 'GPF2: a new chickpea variety for the North Western Plain Zone of India RK Gumber, TS Sandhu, S Singh, MM Verma, HS Brar… - International Chickpea and Pigeonpea Newsletter, 1995', '1995', 'RK Gumber, TS Sandhu, S Singh, MM Verma, HS Brar, JS Sandhu, TS Bains, AS Gill, K Singh', 'International Chickpea and Pigeonpea Newsletter', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13345', 0, 'Exploiting reciprocity toward link prediction', 'Journal', 'Guinea pigs were dermally exposed to the hairdye paraphenylenediamine (PPD) for 15 and 30 days to assess the effects on selected enzyme activities, lipid peroxidation, and histamine content in the skin. The activities of acid phosphatase, glutathione-s-transferase, and tyrosinase were enhanced after application of PPD. The lipid peroxidation, histamine, and PPD content of skin also showed marked elevation following dermal exposure to the chemical.', 'Effects of dermal exposure to paraphenylenediamine in guinea pigs AK Mathur, BN Gupta, S Singh, A Singh - Journal of Toxicology: Cutaneous and Ocular …, 1995 Related articles All 4 versions', '1995/1/1', 'AK Mathur, BN Gupta, S Singh, A Singh', 'Journal of Toxicology: Cutaneous and Ocular Toxicology', 'Taylor & Francis', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13346', 0, 'Temporal link prediction in multi-relational network', 'Journal', 'Left ventricular functions were studied by two-dimensional, M-mode, and Doppler echocardiography in 25 multitransfused, nonchelated patients with beta-thalassemia major (group I) and in 15 age-matched healthy children (group II). Hemoglobin levels in the patients had been maintained at over 9gm/dl, and none of them had overt evidence of cardiac failure. The mean ejection fraction (EF) was significantly lower in group I (P<.05). The ratio of early diastolic wave (E) to atrial filling wave (A) i.e., EA ratio was significantly greater (P<.05). Although the mean deceleration time (DT) in group I was greater, the difference was not statistically significant. The prolongation of DT correlated positively with the number of transfusions and the serum ferritin level. The mean systolic and diastolic left ventricular volumes were greater in those with serum ferritin in excess of 2500 ng/ml. Noninvasive, echocardiographic evaluation is …', 'ECHOCARDIOGRAPHIC EVALUATION OF CARDIAC-FUNCTION IN MULTITRANSFUSED NONCHELATED CHILDREN WITH THALASSEMIA S SINGH, A GROVER, RK MARWAHA, G GAREWAL… - INTERNATIONAL JOURNAL OF PEDIATRIC …, 1995', '1995/1/1', 'S SINGH, A GROVER, RK MARWAHA, G GAREWAL, D PRAKASH', 'INTERNATIONAL JOURNAL OF PEDIATRIC HEMATOLOGY/ONCOLOGY', 'HARWOOD ACAD PUBL GMBH, TAYLOR & FRANCIS GROUP', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
