('13375', 0, 'Functional outcomes of sensorimotor balance training as compared to dorsiflexor strengthening in elderly population', 'Book', '[en] Recently, a number of light neutron-rich nuclei, like 11 Li, 14 Be and 17 B, are identified at the neutron-drip line, which show the interesting new structure of forming a kind of halo of the last couple of neutrons around the remaining core nucleus. In the present paper, the authors have studied a highly neutron-rich nucleus 288 104 with a view to identify the possible target-projectile combinations for forming this heavy nucleus at the neutron-drip line. For this purpose, they have calculated the cold fragmentation potential and the formation yields of 288 104 for all the possible target-projectile combinations. Interestingly enough, they find that for cold fusion reactions, in addition to usual one or both closed (or nearly closed) spherical or deformed shell nuclei, 11 Li, 14 Be, 18 C and 22 O are also predicted to be the possible projectiles for forming 288 104. The other cold fusion reactions for forming 288 104 are 130 Cd+ 158 Ba, 98 Kr+ 190 Er, 78 Ni+ 210 Os, 62 Ti+ 226 Pb and 44 S+ 244 Ra. Also, an isotopic dependence of the target-projectile combinations in cold fusion reactions seems evident', 'Cold fusion reactions induced by the light nuclei at neutron-drip line RK Gupta, S Singh - 206th ACS national meeting, 1993', '1993', 'RK Gupta, S Singh', '206th ACS national meeting', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
