('13399', 5, 'Growth and developmental behaviour of Lipaphis erysimi (Kalt.) at leaf and flowering stages on different mustard genotypes.', 'Journal', 'Investigations to study the effect of nitrogen, gibberellic acid and benzyl adenine on yield and quality of onion were conducted during the year 1985-86 and 1996-87 at vegetable Research Farm, Institute of Agricultural Sciences, Banaras Hindu University, Varanasi. Treatment consisted of two levels each of nitrogen, gibberellic acid and benzyl adenine alongwith control. Application of 160 Kg Nha-¹ significantly increased the yield, fresh and dry weight of bulb together with allyl sulphide in both the years of experimentation. Nevertheless, none of the treatments could better TSS of onion bulb. There was a significant decline in vitamin C content owing to application of the different treatments when compared with control.', 'Effect of nitrogen, gibberellic acid and benzyl adenine on yield and quality of onion (Allium Cepa L.) SK Singh, CBS Rajput, SP Singh - Progressive Horticulture, 1992 Cited by 5 Related articles', '1992', 'SK Singh, CBS Rajput, SP Singh', 'Progressive Horticulture', 'HILL HORTICULTURE DEVELOPMENT BOARD', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
