('13405', 6, 'Potential role of host tree species in determining the composition of polysaccharides of Ganoderma lucidum (Fr.) Karst.(GLPS)', 'Journal', 'One hundred ninety one children below 5 years of age suffering from poliomyelitis were analyzed to find out the immunization status and its correlation with the incidence of poliomyelitis. Effects of age, sex, immunization status and seasonal variation on the morbidity and mortality status were studied. The maximum number of cases were admitted during the months of July (23.6%) and August (23.1%). Of 191 cases, 143 (74.9%) had no immunization and 48 (25.1%) were partially immunized. A total of 155 (81.2%) cases had spinal polio, 23 (12.01%) bulbo-spinal polio, and 13 had (6.8%) bulbar polio. Serious illness (bulbospinal and bulbar type) was more in partially immunized children (25%) as compared to unimmunized children (16.8%). The mortality rate was more than two times higher in the partially immunized (29.6%) as compared to unimmunized children (11.2%). The possible explanation for high mortality in partially immunized children could be due to the adverse effect of OPV which has not been studied so far.', 'Poliomyelitis with special reference to immunization status. GP Mathur, S Mathur, V Gupta, M Bhalla, JN Bhalla… - Indian pediatrics, 1991 Cited by 6 Related articles All 5 versions', '1991/6/1', 'GP Mathur, S Mathur, V Gupta, M Bhalla, JN Bhalla, VN Tripathi, SM Kini, S Singh', 'Indian pediatrics', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13406', 0, 'Human resource management in India: strategy, performance and complementarity', 'nan', 'This patent describes an exhaust cleaner and burner system for use with the exhaust system of an internal combustion engine. It comprises: an exhaust conduit for receiving exhaust gas from the engine, having an inlet and an outlet; a diverter valve disposed at the outlet for selectively directing exhaust flow through a first, main branch when open and a second, bypass branch when closed; exhaust filter means having an inlet connected to the main branch and an outlet connected to the exhaust system; burner means having an outlet mounted upstream of the filter means and operable to raise the temperature of the filter means, the burner means comprising a burner supply conduit for supplying exhaust gas to the burner. The burner supply conduit having an inlet end connected to the exhaust conduit, an outlet end connected to the burner means and a metering orifice disposed within the burner supply conduit, between the inlet end and the outlet end; the system operable, during normal engine operation, to open the diverter valve and pass exhaust gas through the filter means, and operable, upon reaching a predetermined condition, to close the diverter valve and pass exhaust gas through the bypass branch and means for maintaining a predetermined pressure in the exhaust conduit to provide a substantially constant supply of exhaust gas to the burner means through the burner supply conduit; and wherein the burner means is operable to raise the temperature of the exhaust gas to a level sufficient to burn particulates accumulated on the filter thereby regenerating the filter.', 'Particulate system for an internal combustion engine JM Lopez-Crevillen, S Singh, AD Tuteja - 1991', '1991/1/29', 'JM Lopez-Crevillen, S Singh, AD Tuteja', 'nan', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
