('13409', 5, 'Frosting Effect on Potato and its management', 'Journal', 'This study was undertaken and completed in 1988, in an attempt to determine the reasons for admission to hospital, and the optimum care required for patients with Human Immunodeficiency Virus related illnesses. Approximately half of the total medical admissions stayed for less than a week, and patients admitted for terminal care and social care occupied a relatively small proportion of the beds. The single largest group of admissions were those for inpatient management of AIDS-related pneumonias. The results of this study provide a greater understanding of the resources currently required for such care, and suggest initiatives for meeting future needs.', 'Model of care for the hospital treatment of individuals with HIV infection. S Singh, D Hawkins, M Connolly, B Gazzard - Health Trends, 1991 Cited by 5 Related articles All 2 versions', '1991/1/1', 'S Singh, D Hawkins, M Connolly, B Gazzard', 'Health Trends', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13410', 1, 'Secure and efficient integrity algorithm based on existing SHA algorithms', 'Journal', 'Inclusion of fibre reinforcement in concrete, mortar or cement paste can enhance many of its engineering properties such as flexural strength, fracture toughness, resistance to fatigue, impact and thermal shock or spalling. The degree of enhancement of the properties of hardened concrete depends upon the type, size, shape, volume fraction, and aspect ratio of the fibres. Flexural fatigue strength and endurance limit are important design considerations for structures subjected to repeated live (dynamic) loads. Typical examples are highway and airfield pavements, bridges, off-shore constructions, machine foundations, blast and earthquake resistant structures. A comprehensive review of investigations conducted on fatigue behaviour of fibre reinforced concrete is presented. Important effects of fibers typically of steel and polypropylene on fatigue behaviour of concrete are discussed.', 'Fatigue Behaviour of Fibre Reinforced Concrete SP Singh, ML Gambhir, CB Kukreja - Oxford & IBH Publishing Co. Pvt. Ltd.(India),, 1991 Cited by 1 Related articles All 2 versions', '1991', 'SP Singh, ML Gambhir, CB Kukreja', 'Oxford & IBH Publishing Co. Pvt. Ltd.(India),', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
