('13418', 0, 'EFFECT OF PRE-EXISTING JUXTA-ARTICULAR OSTEOPENIA IN PATIENTS UNDERGOING TOTAL KNEE REPLACEMENT', 'Journal', 'The paper seeks to identify the nature and impact of factors affecting overdues of agricultural loans in Agra District, Uttar Pradesh, India. The study was conducted in Bichpuri Block of Agra, selected for its socioeconomic suitability. An econometric analysis was carried out in which the operational size of holdings, amount borrowed, amount of loans diverted to unproductive purposes, repayment capacity, cropping intensity, the magnitude of family expenditure and the ratio of dependants are all regressed against the magnitude of loans overdues. It is suggested that the amount borrowed, the amount diverted into unproductive uses, the size of holdings and repayment capacity are all important factors affecting loans overdues.', 'An analysis of factors affecting overdues of agricultural loans-a study in Agra District of Uttah Pradesh. SP Singh, AK Jain - Indian Cooperative Review, 1990 All 2 versions', '1990', 'SP Singh, AK Jain', 'Indian Cooperative Review', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13419', 1, 'CONCURRENT CHEMORADIATION THERAPY CONFERS BETTER SURVIVAL OUTCOMES IN PATIENTS WITH LOW BASELINE HPV TITRES.', 'Journal', 'Information on heritability, genetic advance and correlations is derived from data on seed yield, its components and oil content from 45 F 1 s and F 2 s from a 10 parent diallel without reciprocals. High heritability and high genetic advance were estimated for primary branches/plant, seed yield, oil content, capitula/plant and 100-seed weight in both generations. Oil content was negatively associated with seed yield and 100-seed weight but positively with maturity traits.', 'Genetic studies in relation to the improvement of oil content and seed yield in safflower (Carthamus tinctorius L.). RK Gupta, SP Singh - Genetika (Beograd), 1990 Cited by 1 Related articles', '1990', 'RK Gupta, SP Singh', 'Genetika (Beograd)', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
