('13448', 0, 'Exploiting reciprocity toward link prediction', 'Journal', '1er. Resumen: Se aplicaron 0, 30, 45 o 90 kg de N/ha a Panicum maximum sembrada en macetas, con o sin inoculacion con Azospirillum brasilense. Se efectuaron 3 cortes; despues de cada corte, se midieron los rendimentos de MS fresca y la PC. Estos 2 parametros aumentaron en los 3 cortes con el aumento en la tasa de N. La respuesta en rendimiento de materia fresca de P. maximum a la inoculacion con A. brasilense fue significativa; estos aumentaron en 94, 99 y 103 por ciento en el primer, segundo y tercer cortes, resp., en comparacion con el testigo. Los efectos beneficos de N mas inoculacion fueron mayores en terminos de rendimiento de materia verde con todas las tasas de N y el rendimiento de PC y MS con las tasas bajas de N; en el tercer corte, los rendimientos de PC y MS de de la graminea aumentaron hasta 25 y 50 por ciento, resp., en asociacion con A. brasilense, lo que indica que el efecto asociativo de A. brasilense disminuye en el tercer corte. Hubo poca diferencia entre los rendimientos de MS, PC y materia verde, con o sin inoculacion, con 90 kg de N/ha.(CIAT).', 'Effect of inoculation with Azospirillum brasilense on yield and quality of guinea grass. TK Ganguli, S Singh - Indian Journal of Dairy Science, 1988 All 2 versions', '1988', 'TK Ganguli, S Singh', 'Indian Journal of Dairy Science', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13449', 2, 'Temporal link prediction in multi-relational network', 'Journal', 'Forty genotypes of mungbean (Vigna radiata (L.) Wilczek) were grown in four environments: the summer and kharif seasons under narrow (10 cm x 20 cm) and wide (10 cm x 30 cm) spacings in a randomized block design with three replications. Each plot had three rows of 4 m length and yield data (g) was recorded on the middle row of each plot. The data on G x E interaction was utilized for selecting desirable genotypes with respect to their pattern of responses based on parametric (regression coefficients and deviations from regression) and nonparametric approaches (standardized distance). In the parametric approach, the linear regression of 26 genotypes was found significant. For seven genotypes regression\'coefficients. deviated significantly from unity. ML 370 and MUM 3 had regression approaching unity with high mean performance and are, therefore, recommended for commercial cultivation. In the nonparametric approach, standardized distances for similarity of responses were estimated among 780 pairs of genotypes. The genotypes were grouped into nine clusters. The divergent genotypes of the same cluster are recommended for use in crossing programs to generate high-yielding genotypes showing responses similar to their parents. A quantitative mathematical characterization and qualitative description of genotypes as like or unlike other genotypes by adopting nonparametric clustering procedures are suggested.', 'Clustering of isoresponsive genotypes in mungbean (Vigna radiata (L.) Wilczek) using parametric and non parametric approaches SP Singh - Proc. Second International Symposium, held at …, 1988 Cited by 2 Related articles All 3 versions', '1988', 'SP Singh', 'Proc. Second International Symposium, held at Bangkok, Thailand', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13450', 0, 'Mining heterogeneous terrorist attack network using personalized PageRank', 'Journal', 'In a field study, the bio-efficacy and crop selectivity of six promising herbicides Alachlor, Metribuzin, Oxadiazon, Pendimethalin, Fluazifop-butyl, and Acifluorfen were evaluated in lentil sown after rice under zero tillage. Metribuzin, Oxadiazon, and Pendimethalin controlled most weeds and significantly reduced their number and dry matter. However, Oxadiazon and Pendimethalin were found phytotoxic to lentil. The grain yield obtained under Metribuzin compared well with that obtained with repeated weedings', 'Studies on weed control in lentil sown after rice under zero tillage [Lens culinaris] S Singh, KC Gautam, R Prasad - Lentil Experimental News Service, 1988', '1988', 'S Singh, KC Gautam, R Prasad', 'Lentil Experimental News Service', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
