('13464', 0, 'Elevated Levels of IL-6 and IL-8 Have Predictive Role in the Development of Respiratory Failure in Patients With Acute Pancreatitis', 'Journal', 'The effects of defoliation on seed yield and its components in faba bean were investigated by removing all leaves, some leaves from different plant parts, and topping of plants. Undefoliated crop had significantly higher seed yield than all defoliated treatments. The number of pods/plant decreased consistently with increasing defoliation. Defoliation of the shoot apex at 90, 105, and 120 days after sowing did not influence seed yield as much as yield attributing characters. Among the treatments involving partial defoliation, removal of leaves fro1415m the upper third of the plant resulted in a greater reduction in seed yield compared with leaf removal from the middle third of the plant during both years of the experiment and from the lower third during the first', 'Defoliation studies in faba bean [Vicia faba] SP Singh, NP Singh, RK Pandey - Faba Bean Information Service, 1987 All 2 versions', '1987', 'SP Singh, NP Singh, RK Pandey', 'Faba Bean Information Service', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13465', 2, 'Synthesis and biological evaluation of 1, 3, 6-trisubstituted β-carboline derivatives for cytotoxic and anti-leishmanial potential', 'Journal', 'Presence of aflatoxin B sub(1), B sub(2), G sub(1) and G sub(2) in the feed is potentially one of the most serious problem. Among the feed ingredients analysed only groundnut cake was found to be the major feed component affected by aflatoxin. In the feedstuffs the overall incidence of aflatoxin was 30.76%. The predominant fungi infesting these feeds were Aspergillus flavus, A. niger) and species of Fusarium, Penicillium, Rhizopus and Curvularia . Since these toxins remain as residues in poultry meat and eggs continuous monitoring and quality control of the feeds should be undertaken by the feed manufacturers.', 'Incidence of aflatoxin in poultry feeds. S Singh - Poultry Adviser, 1987 Cited by 2 Related articles', '1987', 'S Singh', 'Poultry Adviser', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13466', 0, 'Sugarcane seed composition and changes during artificial ageing', 'Conference', 'Extensive studies on host plant resistance to cowpea pests were undertaken at the International Institute of Tropical Agriculture (IITA) [Nigeria] during the last two decades. The results for cowpea are discussed and projections made on the prospects of developing host plant resistance in other grain legume species. Progress to date in developing resistance to disease and insect pests is described. Research efforts continue to concentrate on the development of host plant resistance as the central component of effective pest control and management strategies.', 'Projections on the prospects of host plant resistance to pests in grain legumes: focus on cowpea Vigna unguiculata (L.) Walp. SR Singh - 11. International Congress of Plant Protection, Manila …, 1987', '1987', 'SR Singh', '11. International Congress of Plant Protection, Manila (Philippines), 5-9 Oct 1987', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
