('13502', 7, 'Growth and developmental behaviour of Lipaphis erysimi (Kalt.) at leaf and flowering stages on different mustard genotypes.', 'nan', 'The rather neglected story of India\'s violent revolutionaries in the nationalist period, inside and outside India, has gradually been trickling out in the last few decades. Since many of the revolutionaries worked secretly and not all of their plans came to fruition, it has been hard to learn of their work unless they wrote memoirs, were carefully tracked by the CID, or were interviewed by scholars prepared to tell their tales. These two books make a contribution to this fascinating story of secret plotting, organization, assassination, and uprising. SC Sen Gupta\'s work is largely the tale of the Bengal Volunteers (BV), is based on extensive testimony of survivors, and is written with verve and passion. This is a group about which little is known and so the author has preserved their history for posterity. Led by Hem Chandra Ghosh from the early twentieth century, the group was called the Mukti Sangha and later the Bengal …', 'Buried Alive: Autobiography, Speeches and Writings of an Indian Revolutionary A Singh, P Singh - 1984 Cited by 7 Related articles', '1984', 'Ajit Singh, Pardaman Singh', 'nan', 'Gitanjali', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
