('13504', 0, 'Improved Biodistribution and Efficiency of Endogenous Radiotherapy by Means of Functionalized Hydrophilic Nanogels', 'Journal', 'The propagation of Bleustein–Gulyaev waves in the presence of a dc electric field in the vacuum baked piezoelectric semiconducting crystals of class 6 has been studied theoretically. By solving the partial differential equations representing the electron–acoustic wave interaction in the piezoelectric semiconducting region, and the Laplace’s equation in the vacuum region separately and fulfilling the relevant boundary conditions, we obtain an expression for the amplification coefficient. The effects of carrier diffusion, resistivity, and carrier drift velocity on the amplification coefficient have been studied based on numerical calculations for the semiconducting CdS sample. It has been observed that, compared to Rayleigh waves, the Bleustein–Gulyaev waves give a much higher amplification.', 'Amplification of Bleustein–Gulyaev waves in cadmium sulfide P Palanichamy, SP Singh - Journal of applied physics, 1983 Related articles All 4 versions', '1983/12', 'P Palanichamy, SP Singh', 'Journal of applied physics', 'American Institute of Physics', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13505', 0, 'Organic Farming: A need of sustainable agriculture', 'Journal', 'A development history is presented for the Communication Payload of the Ariane Passenger Payload Experiment (APPLE) geosynchronous satellite, which had to meet stringent technological and scheduling requirements. The APPLE spacecraft objectives have allowed the gaining of expertise in communication payload design that is applicable to the Indian National Satellite system. Payload subsystems were developed separately, and the communication transponder was devised after their integration. Attention is given to a quality assurance program, encompassing all aspects of material and component selection, design, fabrication, and testing and evaluation. Design work began in 1977, and an engineering model was completed by the end of 1978.', 'Payload for the first experimental Indian communication satellite\'APPLE\' L Lasrado, V Ramiah, PNR Shetty, NS Pillai, SK Singh… - Aeronautical Society India Journal, 1983 All 3 versions', '1983/11', 'L Lasrado, V Ramiah, PNR Shetty, NS Pillai, SK Singh, B Singh, RK Gupta, VK Garg, R Saxena, R Singh', 'Aeronautical Society India Journal', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13506', 0, 'Small producers, knowledge and markets', 'Journal', 'The thermodynamic perturbation theory in which all angle-dependent interactions are considered as a perturbation of the central potential is applied to study the equilibrium properties of a fluid composed of non-axial molecules. The influence of a large number of anisotropic pair and three-body non-additive interactions have been taken into account. Using the same set of force parameters the calculation is made for gaseous pressure second and third virial coefficients and liquid phase thermodynamic properties (Helmholtz free-energy, configurational energy, pressure and entropy). It is shown that the non-axial approximation is an improvement over the axial one. Excellent agreement between theory and experiment is obtained for ethylene.', 'Perturbation theory for non-axial molecular fluids S Singh, UP Singh, Y Singh - Physica A: Statistical Mechanics and its Applications, 1983 Related articles All 7 versions', '1983/9/1', 'S Singh, UP Singh, Y Singh', 'Physica A: Statistical Mechanics and its Applications', 'North-Holland', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13507', 5, 'Studies on seasonal abundance of mushroom flies', 'Journal', 'Acoustic second harmonic generation is studied theoretically in nondegenerate piezoelectric semiconductors in the presence of dc electric field longitudinal to the direction of propagation of the acoustic wave. The static electric‐field intensity and the carrier concentration inside the semiconductor are taken as nonuniform even in trap‐free samples. This assumption used in our theory modifies the results obtained by the earlier theories considerably. It is also found that the power thus calculated for the second harmonic flux in terms of the power associated with the fundamental flux is enhanced. Comparison with the available experimental results shows a qualitative agreement. We have used the phenomenological theory and that restricts our analysis to the low frequency region.', 'Acoustic second harmonic generation in piezoelectric semiconductors: Effect of nonuniform electric field intensity P Palanichamy, SP Singh - Journal of applied physics, 1983 Cited by 5 Related articles All 4 versions', '1983/7', 'P Palanichamy, SP Singh', 'Journal of applied physics', 'American Institute of Physics', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
