('13588', 0, 'Simulation of various adaptive techniques in wireless: A comprehensive view', 'Journal', 'The suitability of stored seeds of 11 cultivars of Pennisetum americanum (typhoides) for the development of Sitotroga cerealella (Ol.) and Sitophilus oryzae (L.) was assessed in the laboratory in New Delhi, India, at 65% RH and 26-28 deg C. The seeds were graded into large (\'bold\'), medium and small sizes, and the weight of healthy seeds, weight of damaged seeds, adult emergence, mean development period, adult weight, average number of kernels required per adult of Sitotroga and percentage of food utilisation were recorded. While over 60% of Sitotroga completed their development, only 20% of Sitophilus survived to the adult stage. The data on insect weight and mean development period were compared with those for other food-plants such as wheat, maize and barley. Large seeds of P. americanum were utilised by both insect species and compared well with wheat; the degree of infestation depended on the proportion of seeds weighing over 14 mg each.', 'Developmental response of different pearlmillet cultivar seeds to Sitotroga cerealella Olivier and Sitophilus oryzae (Linn.). TD Yadav, S Singh - Bulletin of Entomology, 1980 All 2 versions', '1980', 'TD Yadav, S Singh', 'Bulletin of Entomology', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
