('13594', 0, 'Biology of phorid fly, Megaselia agarici on button mushroom Agaricus bisporus', 'Conference', 'Catharanthus roseus has recently came into prominence as a new source of vital drugs employed in treatment of cancer and high blood pressure. Despite its introduction into cultivation of several southeast Asian countries, neither high yielding lines nor improved cultivation practices are determined. Thus, improvement studies on this crop were taken up at the Bureau and the results are presented here. The crop exhibit, variation in colour of flowers such as pink, white and several intermediate forms. We hold collections from wild growing populations found in coastal tracts of India and data on their evaluation for several economic traits are presented. In general, pink flowered plants gave higher yield and white flower types were found succeptible to mycoplasma disease. The crop yield was considerably increased on containing reproductive phase by defloration and detopping. However, detopping was found better and gave 63% and 58% higher foliage and root yield, the increase in alkaloid in root was around 20%. Further there was an alround increase in yield on nitrogen application. However, the overall yield was 40; higher at 80 kg/ha level whereas increase in total alkaloids content more or less stabilized at 40 kg/ha level. Age is another parameter which affected crop yield. An overall increase in yield was registered from 200 days onwards to 290 days. The root yield was significantly high up to 260 days age and basal stems increased further progressively till 290 days. The foliage yield, on the contrary, showed a downward trend till 260 days but rose significantly if harvesting was delayed up to 290 days. The interaction between N and age …', 'Crop improvement studies in Catharanthus roseus for higher yield SK Pareek, S Singh, VK Srivastava - 4. Asian Symposium on Medicinal Plants and Spices …, 1980', '1980', 'SK Pareek, S Singh, VK Srivastava', '4. Asian Sympo