('13596', 1, 'Studies of neurosecretory cells of eyestalk, brain and thoracic ganglia of Metapenaeus dobsoni (Miers, 1878) in relation to ovarian maturation', 'Journal', 'A study of bacterial flora and their sensitivity to various antibiotics was carried out in 144 infants and children out of which 20 cases did not show any growth of organisms on culture. Pseudomonas was the commonest strain isolated: the rest of the organisms were Proteus,Staphylococcus albus, Staphylococcus aureus, E. coli, Streptococcus viridans, Klebsiellas and diphtheroids in order of frequency. Gentamicin was found to be the most effective antibiotic against most of the pathogenic bacteria.', 'Bacteriology of chronic middle ear otorrhoea in infants and children SC Gupta, SR Singh, RC Pande, V Kumar - Indian Journal of Pediatrics, 1979 Cited by 1 Related articles All 6 versions', '1979/11', 'SC Gupta, SR Singh, RC Pande, Vinay Kumar', 'Indian Journal of Pediatrics', 'Springer India', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13597', 2, 'A comparative study to evaluate the efficacy and safety of single dose intravenous iron carboxymaltose vs multidose iron sucrose in postpartum cases of severe iron deficiency …', 'Journal', 'Prepubertal Punjabi girls ranging in age from 16 to 12 years and belonging to lower and lower-middle socio-economic groups were included in the study. The data on 692 girls for weight, height and sitting height were collected during 1974–75 from various schools of Patiala city. The differences in body weight, height and sitting height at various ages among different birth ranking girls are non-significant. The physical growth patterns among different groups are almost similar. The home environment which can reasonably be assumed to be better for the first child has little if any impact on the physical growth of Punjabi girls.', 'Order of birth and growth in weight and height of Punjabi girls from 6 to 12 years SP Singh, HS Sodhi - The Indian Journal of Pediatrics, 1979 Cited by 2 Related articles All 5 versions', '1979/10', 'SP Singh, HS Sodhi', 'The Indian Journal of Pediatrics', 'Springer India', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
