('13615', 4, 'Frosting Effect on Potato and its management', 'Journal', 'In a recent contribution to this journal [1], Khalil obtained the first passage time distribution to system failure and mean time to system failure for a 2-unit cold-standby redundant system with random switchover and two types of repair. The purpose of this paper is to obtain several other important reliability characteristics, eg (i) pointwise availability and unavailability,(ii) expected number of system failures during (0, t],(iii) joint distribution of first up time and down time,(iv) sojourn time distribution of system down this is deduced as a marginal distribution,(v) mean down time,(vi) steady state behaviour of the system. The analysis is carried out with the help of renewal theoretic arguments by identifying suitable regeneration points, refer Kapur and Kapoor [2-4] and Nakagawa and Osaki [5]. We deduce the results of Khalil [1] and Nakagawa and Osaki [5, 6] as particular cases of our results.', 'Two-unit redundant system with random switchover time and two types of repair SP Singh, PK Kapur, KR Kapoor - Microelectronics Reliability, 1979 Cited by 4 Related articles All 2 versions', '1979/1/1', 'SP Singh, PK Kapur, KR Kapoor', 'Microelectronics Reliability', 'Pergamon', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13616', 0, 'Secure and efficient integrity algorithm based on existing SHA algorithms', 'Journal', 'Laboratory studies were conducted to find out the changes in the different forms of manganese and Fe+ 2 due to submergence of some rice growing soils of eastern Uttar Pradesh. Surface soil samples (0-15 cm depth) collected from four fields put to rice cultivation every year, were air-dried and crushed to pass through a 20 mesh sieve. The properties of these soils are given in table 1. These soils remain waterlogged for a period of four to six months in a year. The soils (10 g for Mn and 5 g for Fe) contained in several 30 ml specimen tubes were waterlogged to a depth of 5 cm and incubated in dark at room temperature. Duplicate samples were drawn at the start of the experiment and at intervals of 1, 2, 3, 5, 7 and 12 weeks for the estimation of water soluble, exchangeable, active and inactive Fe and water soluble, exchangeable, easily reducible and active Mn (Motomura & Yokoi 1969; Jackson 1967). Data in table 2 …', 'Transformation of Iron and Manganese in Submerged Rice Soils S Singh, P Ram - Journal of the Indian Society of Soil Science, 1979 Related articles All 3 versions', '1979', 'S Singh, Pati Ram', 'Journal of the Indian Society of Soil Science', 'Indian Society of Soil Science', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13617', 0, 'CFD Analysis and Enhancement Of Heat Transfer In Rectangular Channel Using Blockage with Elongated Hole', 'Journal', 'The heat conduction equation has been solved for evaluation of thermal conductivity of soil by overspecifying the usual boundary conditions in terms of heat flux at the boundary surface. For the determination of thermal conductivity, heat flux needs to be measured at any one time instant ‘t0’ and the variation of the boundary temperature with time. With the knowledge of the heat capacity of soil, thermal conductivity value is explicitly obtained.', 'Solution of Heat Flow Equation for Calculation of Thermal Conductivity of Soil from Heat Flux Measurements SR Singh, BK Sinha - Journal of the Indian Society of Soil Science, 1979 Related articles All 5 versions', '1979', 'SR Singh, BK Sinha', 'Journal of the Indian Society of Soil Science', 'Indian Society of Soil Science', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
