('13626', 0, 'URINARY LEVELS OF C-TERMINAL CROSSLINKED TELOPEPTIDE TYPE 1 AS A DIAGNOSTIC INDICATOR OF KNEE OSTEOARTHRITIS', 'Journal', 'Relative photosynthetic contribution of different plant orsans to the final grain yield in bajra (P. typhoides) were worked out by employing yield reduction and radio tracer techniques. About 60% of the final grain yield was built up due to the assimilatory acti vitiesofthe ear (10%) and the leaves (50%) and 25% was contributed by the leaf sheaths and stem surface. Upper five leaves made larger contribution to the grain yield than the lower ones;: flag leaf alone contributed (13%) as much as the tbtal contribution of all the lower leaves below 5th leaf. The data suggest that the ear of bajra draws upon the photo synthates from almost every photosynthesising plant organ during grain filling period.', 'CONTRIBUTION OF DIFFERENT PHOTOSYNTHETIC SITES TO GRAIN YIELD IN PENN/SETUM TYPHOIDES SP Singh, DVM RAo - Indian journal of plant physiology, 1978 All 3 versions', '1978/1/1', 'SP Singh, DVM RAo', 'Indian journal of plant physiology', 'INDIAN SOC PLANT PHYSIOL', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
