('13670', 2, 'Elevated Levels of IL-6 and IL-8 Have Predictive Role in the Development of Respiratory Failure in Patients With Acute Pancreatitis', 'Journal', 'A phenomenological theory is developed to study acoustic wave second harmonic generation in piezoelectric as well as nonpiezoalectric semiconductors, and derive optimum conditions for maximum harmonic generation. The results show that second harmonic flux is maximum at higher frequencies in nonpiezoelectric semiconductors, and at lower frequencies in semiconductors exhibiting both piezoelectricity and deformation potential, as compared to the case of pure piezoelectric materials, while it is a maximum at v d = v s for both the coupling mechanisms.', 'Acoustic Harmonic Generation in Nondegenerate Semiconductors SP Singh, AK Agarwal - Acta Acustica united with Acustica, 1975 Cited by 2 Related articles All 2 versions', '1975/5/1', 'SP Singh, AK Agarwal', 'Acta Acustica united with Acustica', 'S. Hirzel Verlag', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
('13671', 5, 'Synthesis and biological evaluation of 1, 3, 6-trisubstituted β-carboline derivatives for cytotoxic and anti-leishmanial potential', 'Journal', 'The energy−dependent relaxation time has been incorporated in the study of stimulated electron−phonon−photon interactions in nondegenerate semiconductors in the presence of the external dc electric field. The Boltzmann transfer equation has been used to obtain the gain constant. The results show that the percentage change in the gain constant is ∼15% (for ql<1, Eac=3 V/cm, Ω/ω=0.1, <vd>=1.5 vs) and ∼30% (for ql≳1, Eac=30 V/cm, Ω/ω=2, <vd>=2.0 vs) for moderate strengths of oscillating electromagnetic field (OEF). For weak OEF (Eac<ωvs/Ωμ for ql<1 and Eac <mΩ2/qe for ql≳1), no significant percentage change is observed in the gain constant in both frequency domains.', 'Stimulated electron− phonon− photon interactions in nondegenerate semiconductors considering energy− dependent carrier relaxation time AK Agarwal, SK Sharma, SP Singh, SK Virmani - Journal of Applied Physics, 1975 Cited by 5 Related articles All 3 versions', '1975/2', 'AK Agarwal, SK Sharma, SP Singh, SK Virmani', 'Journal of Applied Physics', 'American Institute of Physics', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
