('13769', 0, 'Influence of edge weight on node proximity based link prediction methods: an empirical analysis', 'Journal', 'Usar soils were collected both from cultivated and virgin sites having poor as well as good surface drainage conditions. Total phosphorus in the drained soils averaged 905 ppm in the surface horizons and 805 ppm in the sub horizons while in the poorly drained soils it averaged 488 ppm on the surfaee and inc-reased down the profile to the extent of 1118 ppm. The virgin profiles contained inore total phosphorus than the cultivated ones. The average values of surface horizons of virgin and cult-ivated profiles were 1157 and 635 ppm for drained and 615 and 403 ppm for poorly drained profiles respectively. The organic P as percent of total P was more in surface horizons and decreased with depth. The organic P was low in well drained soil than in poorly drained soils, the amount being 5.2 and 7.0 percent of the total respectively. The cultivated profiles contained more organic P both in poor and well drained conditions than the virgin ones, the average values expressed as percent of total P of virgin and cultivated soils were 7.1 and 3.3 for drained and 9.0 and 4.1 for poorly drained profiles resp. cti-vely. The organic phosphorus persent in soil organic matter plays an important role in providing the growing crops atleast a part of their phosphate. The amounts and proportions of this form vary widely. Thompson et al (195-1) and Williams and Steinbergs (1958) reported that P content of the organic matter tended to be lower when the pH was above 7. Many workers have', 'Communicated by Dr. Sant singh S Singh, ML Gupta - The Journal of Scientific Research, 1966 Related articles', '1966', 'S Singh, ML Gupta', 'The Journal of Scientific Research', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
