('13776', 1, 'Dr. Kalam-an idea, vision and dream', 'Journal', 'Nitrogen at 100 Ib./acre and P 2 O 6 at 100 Ib./acre were applied at planting time, and Mo as ammonium molybdate at 2 Ib./acre and B as boric acid at 5 Ib./acre were applied to the soil, or as a spray combined with soap solution, when tillering was completed (3 months). Fertilization with N and spraying with the micro-nutrients increased cane yield and the protein content of the plants.-Sugarcane Res. Stat., Jullundur Cantt, Punjab.', 'Effect of boron and molybdenum in the presence of inorganic and organic nitrogen on the yield and quality of sugarcane. H Singh, R De, S Singh - Indian Journal of Sugarcane Research and …, 1960 Cited by 1 Related articles', '1960', 'H Singh, Rajan De, Seva Singh', 'Indian Journal of Sugarcane Research and Development', 'nan', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
